["Paranoid" by Osama & Black Sabbath playing]

2
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:00:51.747 --> 00:00:54.619
[men shouting]

4
00:01:01.496 --> 00:01:02.496
[music concludes]

5
00:01:03.889 --> 00:01:05.848
[speaking Japanese] You've let me down badly.

6
00:01:08.155 --> 00:01:10.505
You know what you have to do.

7
00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:14.074
You're not serious. boss.

8
00:01:14.726 --> 00:01:17.816
I was planning to kill all of you.

9
00:01:18.556 --> 00:01:21.211
But I'll give you a second chance.

10
00:01:21.385 --> 00:01:23.170
If you show me how sorry you are.

11
00:01:24.562 --> 00:01:26.303
An offering for a job.

12
00:01:28.697 --> 00:01:29.872
You can't do it?

13
00:01:30.525 --> 00:01:32.614
[breathes heavily]

14
00:01:43.494 --> 00:01:45.192
- [knife cuts]
- [grunts]

15
00:01:46.584 --> 00:01:48.717
[breathes heavily]

16
00:01:52.721 --> 00:01:53.722
[grunting]

17
00:02:00.381 --> 00:02:02.078
[stifled scream]

18
00:02:05.037 --> 00:02:06.909
[breathes shakily]

19
00:02:12.958 --> 00:02:13.959
I got it.

20
00:02:14.221 --> 00:02:17.572
I'll do it. I'll do it.

21
00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:24.187
[breathes heavily]

22
00:02:26.755 --> 00:02:27.756
[grunts]

23
00:02:28.409 --> 00:02:31.499
[whimpers]

24
00:02:43.946 --> 00:02:45.948
[breathes shakily]

25
00:02:46.905 --> 00:02:47.950
Ah.

26
00:02:50.126 --> 00:02:51.258
[Yakuza member shouts]

27
00:02:54.086 --> 00:02:55.087
[thuds]

28
00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:08.231
Normal. Minnesota.

29
00:03:10.146 --> 00:03:11.495
[lackey shouting in Japanese]

30
00:03:11.669 --> 00:03:12.844
Normal.

31
00:03:13.236 --> 00:03:15.151
Yakuza boss: Go there and redeem yourself.

32
00:03:15.325 --> 00:03:18.328
["Put Your Hand In The Hand" by Ocean playing]

33
00:03:24.552 --> 00:03:27.294
♪ Put your hand In the hand of the man ♪

34
00:03:27.468 --> 00:03:29.992
♪ Who stilled the water ♪

35
00:03:31.167 --> 00:03:32.516
♪ Put your hand ♪

36
00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:33.517
announcer on radio: In special news.

37
00:03:33.691 --> 00:03:35.171
Normal is celebrating

38
00:03:35.345 --> 00:03:38.218
152 years since the railway came to town.

39
00:03:38.696 --> 00:03:40.829
Weather advisory remains on a high level

40
00:03:41.003 --> 00:03:43.048
- with a winter storm...
- [car horn honking]

41
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:45.113
- looks like it's going to...
- [car horn honking]

42
00:03:45.137 --> 00:03:48.315
♪ By putting your hand In the hand of the man... ♪

43
00:03:51.231 --> 00:03:52.841
Keith: So. how's the motel treating you?

44
00:03:53.015 --> 00:03:55.931
Ulysses: Exactly how you'd expect for 55 bucks a night.

45
00:03:56.105 --> 00:03:57.367
Keith: What'd you do dinner?

46
00:03:57.976 --> 00:04:00.762
I got delivery from the Chinese place.

47
00:04:01.153 --> 00:04:02.198
Chang Lu's?

48
00:04:02.416 --> 00:04:03.634
Is there another one?

49
00:04:04.505 --> 00:04:07.377
No. No. Just Chang Lu's.

50
00:04:07.551 --> 00:04:08.551
[engine starting]

51
00:04:10.728 --> 00:04:13.165
Keith: Have you been to Ernie's place to try his meatloaf?

52
00:04:13.340 --> 00:04:14.341
It's amazing.

53
00:04:15.037 --> 00:04:16.212
Ulysses: Duly noted.

54
00:04:18.519 --> 00:04:20.956
[phone line ringing]

55
00:04:21.348 --> 00:04:22.523
[tone beeps]

56
00:04:22.697 --> 00:04:24.220
Woman on phone: This is Penny.

57
00:04:24.394 --> 00:04:25.850
Sorry I missed you. Please leave a message.

58
00:04:25.874 --> 00:04:27.267
and I'll circle back when I can.

59
00:04:27.441 --> 00:04:29.161
- [tone beeps]
- Ulysses: Hey. it's just me.

60
00:04:29.225 --> 00:04:31.401
Ulysses. you know. your husband.

61
00:04:31.575 --> 00:04:34.056
if you don't mind me still calling myself that.

62
00:04:34.578 --> 00:04:36.537
I know we agreed to take some time apart.

63
00:04:36.711 --> 00:04:38.626
that you need space. I... I get it.

64
00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:40.715
but I just thought I'd let you know

65
00:04:40.889 --> 00:04:43.631
I landed another temporary sheriff job

66
00:04:43.805 --> 00:04:46.547
in a little town called Normal. Minnesota.

67
00:04:47.417 --> 00:04:50.377
Like a lot of small towns. it's half abandoned.

68
00:04:50.725 --> 00:04:52.204
The other half is nice. though.

69
00:04:52.683 --> 00:04:53.858
People seem friendly enough.

70
00:04:54.642 --> 00:04:57.122
They built themselves a real nice little setup here.

71
00:04:57.558 --> 00:04:58.994
considering how hard times are

72
00:04:59.168 --> 00:05:01.213
for most folks in the country right now.

73
00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:03.477
I don't know what their secret is.

74
00:05:03.651 --> 00:05:05.827
but I could do with a serving of it.

75
00:05:06.306 --> 00:05:07.916
Anyway. it's just for eight weeks

76
00:05:08.090 --> 00:05:10.179
till they elect the new permanent lawman.

77
00:05:11.136 --> 00:05:15.097
My goal is to leave this town just the way I found it.

78
00:05:17.055 --> 00:05:18.883
- [leather creaking]
- [radio crackling]

79
00:05:19.057 --> 00:05:20.339
[man speaking indistinctly on radio]

80
00:05:20.363 --> 00:05:21.886
What's the deal with that jacket?

81
00:05:22.060 --> 00:05:25.760
It's pretty cool. huh? I got it to match my chopper.

82
00:05:26.804 --> 00:05:29.241
- I didn't know you had one.
- Oh. no. I don't. not yet.

83
00:05:29.416 --> 00:05:31.243
I'm just saving up.

84
00:05:32.070 --> 00:05:33.724
Figured I'd start with the jacket.

85
00:05:33.898 --> 00:05:34.943
[leather creaking]

86
00:05:35.117 --> 00:05:37.119
Well. it's loud.

87
00:05:37.380 --> 00:05:39.121
Keith: You mean it's too flashy?

88
00:05:39.295 --> 00:05:41.689
No. I mean it... [sighs] ...makes noise.

89
00:05:41.863 --> 00:05:44.126
- It's literally loud.
- [leather creaking]

90
00:05:44.300 --> 00:05:45.954
And I don't think it's regulation.

91
00:05:46.128 --> 00:05:47.434
- Right.
- Ulysses: Sorry.

92
00:05:48.696 --> 00:05:50.219
- I'll just...
- [creaking]

93
00:05:50.393 --> 00:05:52.439
No. no. Just leave it on. Leave it on.

94
00:05:52.613 --> 00:05:54.441
It's cool. It's very cool.

95
00:05:54.615 --> 00:05:55.790
[radio crackling]

96
00:05:55.964 --> 00:05:58.488
Whoa. $16.8 million.

97
00:05:58.662 --> 00:06:01.012
Where the hell did this town get that kind of money?

98
00:06:01.317 --> 00:06:03.406
Community really came together on that one.

99
00:06:04.146 --> 00:06:05.452
Yeah. I would say.

100
00:06:06.627 --> 00:06:07.758
Keith: Hey. Mayor Kibner!

101
00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:09.325
There he is.

102
00:06:15.200 --> 00:06:16.985
I can't wait for the parade next week.

103
00:06:17.159 --> 00:06:18.987
We all dress up. You're going to love it.

104
00:06:19.161 --> 00:06:20.815
I always wanted to be the parade mascot.

105
00:06:20.989 --> 00:06:22.294
but I never got picked.

106
00:06:22.469 --> 00:06:23.469
I'm not bitter. though.

107
00:06:24.601 --> 00:06:27.691
The guys take their bikes pretty seriously here.

108
00:06:28.388 --> 00:06:30.694
My bike's probably going to be a lot like this one.

109
00:06:31.347 --> 00:06:34.045
Jeez. Randy. I wish my girlfriend was that dirty.

110
00:06:34.219 --> 00:06:35.830
Have you got a girlfriend. Sheriff?

111
00:06:36.004 --> 00:06:38.354
No. I've got a wife. She's had it with me.

112
00:06:38.528 --> 00:06:40.568
Keith: Then I'll put an extra sugar in your coffee.

113
00:06:41.009 --> 00:06:42.706
Hey. Tom! How are you?

114
00:06:42.880 --> 00:06:44.480
Hey. Mike. This is America. God damn it.

115
00:06:44.534 --> 00:06:46.188
What's mine is mine. for fuck's sake.

116
00:06:46.362 --> 00:06:47.882
She can't go and talk to me like this.

117
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:50.018
I'm going to go put a pot on.

118
00:06:50.192 --> 00:06:52.392
I feel like Sisyphus pushing a rock up a God damn hill.

119
00:06:52.499 --> 00:06:53.674
What's the problem?

120
00:06:53.848 --> 00:06:55.589
[sighs] Tom's being a Goddamn dick.

121
00:06:55.763 --> 00:06:57.218
- That's the fucking problem.
- Fuck you. you trumped-up...

122
00:06:57.242 --> 00:06:59.549
Whoa! Just communicate the problem to me.

123
00:06:59.723 --> 00:07:01.725
Depends who the fuck you're meant to be.

124
00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:03.988
Well. if I'm reading this badge correctly.

125
00:07:04.162 --> 00:07:05.512
I'm the sheriff.

126
00:07:05.686 --> 00:07:07.054
Yeah. I sure as shit didn't vote for you.

127
00:07:07.078 --> 00:07:08.558
I understand.

128
00:07:08.732 --> 00:07:11.082
You know Sheriff Gunderson died. right? Last week?

129
00:07:11.256 --> 00:07:13.215
This is Ulysses. He's filling in. yeah?

130
00:07:13.389 --> 00:07:15.565
Yeah. I... I heard something about that.

131
00:07:15.739 --> 00:07:17.349
- Well...
- So you're his replacement?

132
00:07:17.524 --> 00:07:18.699
I'm the interim.

133
00:07:19.221 --> 00:07:21.049
It's like a substitute teacher.

134
00:07:21.223 --> 00:07:22.529
For how long?

135
00:07:22.703 --> 00:07:24.226
He's on week one of eight.

136
00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:25.575
Blaine: Morning. peoples!

137
00:07:25.749 --> 00:07:27.189
Sally: Morning. Blaine. Ooh. donuts.

138
00:07:27.229 --> 00:07:28.554
- Hey. Old-fashioned?
- Okay. Well. so.

139
00:07:28.578 --> 00:07:30.101
Carl keeps parking his Goddamn...

140
00:07:30.275 --> 00:07:31.601
- Sally: Carl's his neighbor.
- My neighbor keeps

141
00:07:31.625 --> 00:07:32.819
parking his God damn rig in my driveway.

142
00:07:32.843 --> 00:07:34.236
- It's a tow truck.
- I see.

143
00:07:34.410 --> 00:07:35.735
Sally: Carl has his own tow trucking company.

144
00:07:35.759 --> 00:07:37.239
- has since high school.
- Hey. Mike.

145
00:07:37.413 --> 00:07:39.217
I lived there first. It's my property just as much...

146
00:07:39.241 --> 00:07:40.871
Tom's on a flag lot. so they have to share a driveway.

147
00:07:40.895 --> 00:07:42.220
He's blocking me in! That fucker's taking 70 percent.

148
00:07:42.244 --> 00:07:43.593
Hang on! Hang on!

149
00:07:45.334 --> 00:07:47.118
Look. You want me to drive out there

150
00:07:47.292 --> 00:07:48.732
and sort this out with Carl for you?

151
00:07:48.859 --> 00:07:51.079
Finally. Please.

152
00:07:51.253 --> 00:07:53.777
Okay. Then I best head out there pronto.

153
00:07:54.778 --> 00:07:58.390
Uh. we're good? All righty. Then I'll retire to my boudoir.

154
00:07:58.565 --> 00:07:59.566
Hey.

155
00:08:01.611 --> 00:08:03.221
How's that badge. Sheriff?

156
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:05.485
Keeping it warm for me?

157
00:08:06.137 --> 00:08:08.618
[chuckles] I'm doing my best.

158
00:08:08.792 --> 00:08:11.186
Blaine: [chuckles] Election's in six weeks.

159
00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:12.579
Remember to vote for me.

160
00:08:12.753 --> 00:08:14.145
- Ulysses: Sure.
- [Blaine laughs]

161
00:08:14.319 --> 00:08:17.192
Ulysses: Good people. small problems.

162
00:08:17.366 --> 00:08:20.282
and if my instincts tell me something is seriously amiss.

163
00:08:20.456 --> 00:08:22.066
well. then I'll get involved.

164
00:08:23.285 --> 00:08:26.070
But yeah. I kind of stopped trusting my instincts.

165
00:08:27.202 --> 00:08:29.465
It's not that I don't care anymore. Penny.

166
00:08:29.639 --> 00:08:33.556
It's just. life's a lot easier when you care a little less.

167
00:08:34.557 --> 00:08:36.428
Then again. we are who we are.

168
00:08:47.483 --> 00:08:49.572
Nothing to see here.

169
00:09:20.124 --> 00:09:23.650
[indistinct radio chatter in background]

170
00:09:28.655 --> 00:09:31.179
Oh. there you are. Refill?

171
00:09:31.832 --> 00:09:34.574
What? Oh. Yeah. Sure.

172
00:09:35.009 --> 00:09:36.639
- This is a hell of an armory.
- [coffee pouring]

173
00:09:36.663 --> 00:09:37.663
Yeah.

174
00:09:39.883 --> 00:09:41.102
Is that C4?

175
00:09:41.668 --> 00:09:44.018
Sally: Uh. that... It is. Yeah.

176
00:09:45.149 --> 00:09:46.542
Why do you have that?

177
00:09:47.412 --> 00:09:48.762
I don't know.

178
00:09:48.936 --> 00:09:50.459
After 9/11. Sheriff Gunderson applied

179
00:09:50.633 --> 00:09:53.027
for every anti-terrorism grant available.

180
00:09:53.201 --> 00:09:55.682
Yeah? How much did he spend on training?

181
00:09:55.856 --> 00:09:57.379
[phone ringing]

182
00:09:58.554 --> 00:10:00.194
I should probably get back to the phones.

183
00:10:00.556 --> 00:10:02.819
Well. the door was unlocked.

184
00:10:02.993 --> 00:10:04.342
That's kind of a no-no.

185
00:10:05.082 --> 00:10:07.128
Oh. Sorry about that.

186
00:10:07.302 --> 00:10:10.740
[phone ringing]

187
00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:15.049
Ulysses: Every town has its own little quirks.

188
00:10:15.876 --> 00:10:17.225
You can't change 'em.

189
00:10:17.399 --> 00:10:19.183
Two hundred K. and the instructions

190
00:10:19.357 --> 00:10:20.532
are in Japanese.

191
00:10:21.272 --> 00:10:22.665
Ulysses: The interim job

192
00:10:22.839 --> 00:10:24.319
is not to get in the way of them.

193
00:10:25.276 --> 00:10:28.236
I'm like a midwife with a gun...

194
00:10:28.758 --> 00:10:32.370
[chuckles] ...helping 'em transition smoothly.

195
00:10:38.376 --> 00:10:40.465
[shop bell jingling]

196
00:10:42.076 --> 00:10:45.601
Oh. damn it. Damn it. Hey!

197
00:10:52.521 --> 00:10:53.783
I like the way you law. man.

198
00:10:56.394 --> 00:10:58.092
[wind whooshing]

199
00:11:00.529 --> 00:11:03.184
["Bang Bang" by Janis Martin playing]

200
00:11:05.273 --> 00:11:07.841
♪ I'll trade you my heart For your heart. baby ♪

201
00:11:08.015 --> 00:11:09.973
♪ Give you all My kisses to boot ♪

202
00:11:10.147 --> 00:11:12.715
♪ I'll trade you my heart For your heart baby ♪

203
00:11:12.889 --> 00:11:15.239
♪ Give you all My kisses to boot... ♪

204
00:11:15.413 --> 00:11:17.502
Hey. Sheriff. Welcome to my place.

205
00:11:17.677 --> 00:11:19.200
Oh. you're Ernie?

206
00:11:19.374 --> 00:11:21.265
Yeah. just like my dad and my granddad before me.

207
00:11:21.289 --> 00:11:24.466
Oh. yeah. Tell me. What's the story with the decor?

208
00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:26.618
Well. Granddad started collecting 'em after the war.

209
00:11:26.642 --> 00:11:28.242
and he didn't stop till the day he died.

210
00:11:28.949 --> 00:11:30.341
Any of them loaded?

211
00:11:30.820 --> 00:11:32.700
Wouldn't be much fun if they weren't. would it?

212
00:11:35.433 --> 00:11:38.741
- [chuckles]
- So. what can I get you?

213
00:11:38.915 --> 00:11:40.700
Uh. I heard good things about the meatloaf.

214
00:11:40.874 --> 00:11:42.092
Sure. Coming up.

215
00:11:42.832 --> 00:11:44.660
You got to try the pie before you leave town.

216
00:11:44.834 --> 00:11:46.227
Ulysses: Hmm.

217
00:11:46.401 --> 00:11:47.508
Reporter on TV: Dropping temperatures.

218
00:11:47.532 --> 00:11:49.360
Snow is much more likely.

219
00:11:49.534 --> 00:11:51.121
making this our first big winter storm of the season.

220
00:11:51.145 --> 00:11:52.600
and whoo-whee. does this look like a doozy.

221
00:11:52.624 --> 00:11:55.497
Joe: Fucking weather. Fucking Minnesota.

222
00:11:55.671 --> 00:11:57.693
Reporter on TV: Plans to issue a shelter in place

223
00:11:57.717 --> 00:11:59.675
warning around noon tomorrow.

224
00:12:02.547 --> 00:12:04.724
♪ Bang bang ♪

225
00:12:04.898 --> 00:12:06.073
♪ Bang bang ♪

226
00:12:10.381 --> 00:12:11.861
[animal bellowing]

227
00:12:12.035 --> 00:12:14.951
[metal clattering]

228
00:12:15.125 --> 00:12:16.300
[screams]

229
00:12:16.866 --> 00:12:18.302
[animal bellowing]

230
00:12:18.476 --> 00:12:19.651
[gunshot]

231
00:12:19.826 --> 00:12:21.828
- [animal bellowing]
- [pants]

232
00:12:23.394 --> 00:12:25.309
- [metal clattering]
- [animal bellowing]

233
00:12:45.590 --> 00:12:46.591
[bellows]

234
00:12:48.376 --> 00:12:49.856
[chuckles]

235
00:12:50.030 --> 00:12:53.816
[moose bellowing. moose snorting]

236
00:12:55.557 --> 00:12:57.994
- Ulysses: Say cheese.
- [shutter clicks]

237
00:12:59.082 --> 00:13:00.518
What's going on. Officer?

238
00:13:00.780 --> 00:13:03.870
Uh. I think a moose just stole your paint.

239
00:13:05.828 --> 00:13:08.222
Mike: It is going to be a busy day today.

240
00:13:08.918 --> 00:13:10.920
I wanted to get your stamp of approval

241
00:13:11.094 --> 00:13:12.487
on the parade route.

242
00:13:12.661 --> 00:13:14.402
- Ulysses: Okay.
- There's an intersection

243
00:13:14.576 --> 00:13:17.318
that I think are just a real hornets' nest.

244
00:13:17.971 --> 00:13:19.450
and of course. first.

245
00:13:19.624 --> 00:13:21.931
we have the celebration of life at the sheriff's.

246
00:13:22.976 --> 00:13:26.544
The... former sheriff's. that is.

247
00:13:27.545 --> 00:13:28.938
[sighs]

248
00:13:29.243 --> 00:13:30.873
But you don't have to worry about saying anything.

249
00:13:30.897 --> 00:13:32.265
because the mayor's going to take care of that.

250
00:13:32.289 --> 00:13:34.596
and there will be food. [Chuckles]

251
00:13:34.770 --> 00:13:37.077
It is a potluck. so it should be fun.

252
00:13:37.251 --> 00:13:38.861
- All right.
- [radio squawking]

253
00:13:39.035 --> 00:13:40.796
Sally on radio: Anyone available? There's a situation

254
00:13:40.820 --> 00:13:42.660
with Maynard down at the hardware store. Over.

255
00:13:42.778 --> 00:13:44.954
Ulysses: Most of my time is spent on shenanigans.

256
00:13:45.128 --> 00:13:46.671
- low-stakes stuff.
- Sally on radio: Report's

257
00:13:46.695 --> 00:13:48.262
two assholes screaming at each other.

258
00:13:48.436 --> 00:13:50.307
Ulysses: I get to say "Nothing to see here"

259
00:13:50.481 --> 00:13:51.961
over and over all day.

260
00:13:52.135 --> 00:13:53.702
[both shouting]

261
00:13:53.876 --> 00:13:55.791
All right! Just separate! Separate!

262
00:13:56.705 --> 00:13:58.925
Mike. I need you to escort old Clayton here

263
00:13:59.099 --> 00:14:00.419
from the premises and arrest him!

264
00:14:00.448 --> 00:14:02.058
- For what?
- For being a sumbitch!

265
00:14:02.232 --> 00:14:04.626
Sumbitch? More like thrifty.

266
00:14:04.800 --> 00:14:07.150
Amazon's got these damn near 30 percent off!

267
00:14:07.324 --> 00:14:08.884
Okay. To be fair. Maynard that seems...

268
00:14:08.978 --> 00:14:10.414
Clayton: This is America. damn it.

269
00:14:10.632 --> 00:14:11.415
- The customer is always right.
- Like a fair price.

270
00:14:11.589 --> 00:14:12.590
That's not helping.

271
00:14:12.764 --> 00:14:14.070
Oh. the customer is always right

272
00:14:14.244 --> 00:14:15.308
when he's trying to bankrupt the shop-keep?

273
00:14:15.332 --> 00:14:16.483
No. no. Calm down. Calm down.

274
00:14:16.507 --> 00:14:17.789
Listen. Sheriff. I will be damned

275
00:14:17.813 --> 00:14:19.467
if I'm going to let some old...

276
00:14:19.641 --> 00:14:22.165
Like you need the money! You look like an angry thumb!

277
00:14:22.339 --> 00:14:24.733
Maynard: Go home and be Amazon's bitch. motherfucker!

278
00:14:24.907 --> 00:14:26.126
- Guys.
- [both shouting]

279
00:14:26.300 --> 00:14:28.432
Guys! Guys!

280
00:14:29.520 --> 00:14:32.959
Maybe we just want to bring the temperature down

281
00:14:33.133 --> 00:14:34.612
a little bit

282
00:14:34.786 --> 00:14:38.573
in front of the temporary guest from out of town.

283
00:14:39.704 --> 00:14:40.880
Am I right?

284
00:14:41.184 --> 00:14:43.012
Maybe we should go for a walk. hey?

285
00:14:43.186 --> 00:14:44.840
- Okay! I'm going!
- Huh. Clayton? Okay.

286
00:14:45.014 --> 00:14:46.494
- I'm going!
- Let's go.

287
00:14:46.668 --> 00:14:48.365
Clayton. this is America.

288
00:14:48.539 --> 00:14:50.846
which means you can't walk out of a store without paying.

289
00:14:51.020 --> 00:14:52.563
- That's a good point.
- It's called shoplifting.

290
00:14:52.587 --> 00:14:54.260
Clayton: Maynard. you thieving motherfucker!

291
00:14:54.284 --> 00:14:57.157
Enjoy your long walk in the snow. you geriatric tool!

292
00:14:57.331 --> 00:14:59.376
- Sumbitch!
- Okay. Come on now.

293
00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:00.812
Clayton: Asshole!

294
00:15:01.378 --> 00:15:02.989
How often does that happen?

295
00:15:03.946 --> 00:15:05.469
Once. twice a week if I'm lucky.

296
00:15:05.643 --> 00:15:07.210
and it's not like he needs the money.

297
00:15:07.384 --> 00:15:09.038
He just likes pissing up my leg.

298
00:15:09.212 --> 00:15:11.649
Whoa. There's a lot of locks on that cabinet.

299
00:15:11.823 --> 00:15:12.912
What's going on there?

300
00:15:13.651 --> 00:15:14.739
Stump removers.

301
00:15:15.523 --> 00:15:16.872
Uh. what does that mean?

302
00:15:17.525 --> 00:15:19.919
Old-school stump removers.

303
00:15:21.050 --> 00:15:23.748
I still don't know exactly what you're talking about.

304
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:25.141
Sheriff. come quick!

305
00:15:25.315 --> 00:15:28.144
What? I want to hear your answer.

306
00:15:28.318 --> 00:15:29.754
[door closing. shop bell jingling]

307
00:15:31.539 --> 00:15:33.169
Ulysses: It's the yarn? What... What about it?

308
00:15:33.193 --> 00:15:35.369
It's the yarn. I... I... Look. Look.

309
00:15:35.543 --> 00:15:37.893
I'm sorry. This is your "Sheriff. come quick"?

310
00:15:38.067 --> 00:15:41.201
I ordered pink. and they gave me mauve.

311
00:15:41.375 --> 00:15:42.724
Uh. not to play devil's advocate.

312
00:15:42.898 --> 00:15:44.378
but that is not pink. That is mauve.

313
00:15:44.552 --> 00:15:47.250
Mauve. That's what I said. What should I do?

314
00:15:47.424 --> 00:15:49.344
Well. I... I'm not going to be able to help you.

315
00:15:49.383 --> 00:15:51.515
because they look exactly the same to me.

316
00:15:51.689 --> 00:15:53.474
I'm sorry. I'm color-blind.

317
00:15:54.083 --> 00:15:57.217
All right. Well. unlike you. Sheriff.

318
00:15:57.391 --> 00:15:59.654
my clientele's a bit more discerning.

319
00:15:59.828 --> 00:16:01.395
They're not color-blind. No offense.

320
00:16:01.569 --> 00:16:02.894
- [radio beeping]
- Sally on radio: Mike?

321
00:16:02.918 --> 00:16:04.224
Are you there? Over.

322
00:16:04.398 --> 00:16:06.052
- [radio echoing]
- [feedback squeals]

323
00:16:06.226 --> 00:16:08.073
Mike. come on. Pick up. Are you still with the sheriff?

324
00:16:08.097 --> 00:16:09.533
Is that a police scanner you got?

325
00:16:09.707 --> 00:16:10.882
You keeping tabs on me?

326
00:16:11.057 --> 00:16:14.408
Yes. sir. and a CB radio.

327
00:16:14.582 --> 00:16:17.237
- Ulysses: Oh.
- I get lonely.

328
00:16:17.411 --> 00:16:18.890
- And nosy.
- [beeping]

329
00:16:19.239 --> 00:16:20.718
Copy that. Sally. I'm on my way.

330
00:16:20.892 --> 00:16:21.937
Take care.

331
00:16:24.113 --> 00:16:25.767
Call the fire department next time.

332
00:16:26.420 --> 00:16:28.988
- Oh. I...
- Ulysses: I'm kidding.

333
00:16:29.162 --> 00:16:30.554
[chuckles]

334
00:16:30.728 --> 00:16:32.295
[door closing. shop bell jingles]

335
00:16:32.469 --> 00:16:33.469
[bell tolling]

336
00:16:34.341 --> 00:16:36.145
Ulysses: Your buck goes a lot further out here.

337
00:16:36.169 --> 00:16:37.953
That's for sure.

338
00:16:38.127 --> 00:16:40.782
Gunderson had got himself the Big Mac of McMansions.

339
00:16:40.956 --> 00:16:42.803
He must have issued a hell of a lot of parking tickets

340
00:16:42.827 --> 00:16:44.394
to get that.

341
00:16:44.568 --> 00:16:46.448
So. what do you say about a man like Gunderson?

342
00:16:46.614 --> 00:16:49.399
- He was a son of a bitch.
- [crowd chuckling]

343
00:16:49.573 --> 00:16:51.401
But he was our son of a bitch.

344
00:16:51.575 --> 00:16:53.335
- Mike: Boss?
- He was a great golfer. right?

345
00:16:53.360 --> 00:16:55.275
- Mike: Boss.
- A medium fisherman and...

346
00:16:55.449 --> 00:16:56.754
Ulysses: Oh. What's up?

347
00:16:57.755 --> 00:16:59.105
You got to get in on this.

348
00:16:59.627 --> 00:17:01.803
This is just like Christmas.

349
00:17:01.977 --> 00:17:03.805
You got Pete's meats.

350
00:17:04.675 --> 00:17:06.286
fortune cookies. all you can eat.

351
00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:08.114
You want me to make you a plate?

352
00:17:09.158 --> 00:17:11.987
Uh. not unless I want to end up like Gunderson.

353
00:17:12.161 --> 00:17:13.554
Oh. That reminds me.

354
00:17:16.818 --> 00:17:18.298
I think you should be wearing this.

355
00:17:20.778 --> 00:17:22.519
But I thought you said you had only one.

356
00:17:22.693 --> 00:17:26.697
I did. but when the visitation was over and done with.

357
00:17:26.871 --> 00:17:30.136
I nicked it off of the corpse

358
00:17:31.224 --> 00:17:33.835
before they closed the casket.

359
00:17:34.009 --> 00:17:37.621
So. you enjoy the power while it lasts.

360
00:17:49.459 --> 00:17:51.896
[people chatting in distance]

361
00:17:52.854 --> 00:17:55.204
[suspenseful music playing]

362
00:17:57.989 --> 00:17:59.513
[liquid pouring]

363
00:18:04.257 --> 00:18:06.041
Dr. Velie: Oh. what a trip that was.

364
00:18:06.215 --> 00:18:08.522
Those Japanese sure love their golf.

365
00:18:08.696 --> 00:18:09.784
[chuckles]

366
00:18:11.090 --> 00:18:13.440
So. what'd you pick?

367
00:18:14.354 --> 00:18:16.530
Oh. Uh. Ashford something.

368
00:18:16.704 --> 00:18:21.012
I always tend to lean toward the Irish.

369
00:18:22.013 --> 00:18:23.189
Seven Gs a bottle.

370
00:18:23.754 --> 00:18:24.842
[whistles]

371
00:18:26.670 --> 00:18:28.324
- Dr. Velie.
- Ulysses.

372
00:18:29.369 --> 00:18:32.763
Um. you signed. uh.

373
00:18:32.937 --> 00:18:34.939
Sheriff Gunderson's death certificate. right?

374
00:18:35.679 --> 00:18:37.377
Sadly. yes. I did.

375
00:18:37.986 --> 00:18:39.118
What happened there?

376
00:18:40.336 --> 00:18:43.600
Well. a couple Wednesdays ago. around three in the morning.

377
00:18:43.774 --> 00:18:45.428
Deputy Blaine found him out back

378
00:18:45.602 --> 00:18:47.996
in little more than his tighty-whities.

379
00:18:48.170 --> 00:18:52.392
frozen like a chunk of ice chiseled by a chainsaw.

380
00:18:53.001 --> 00:18:54.872
What do you suppose he thought he was doing?

381
00:18:56.309 --> 00:18:58.789
Not my job to go supposing... [chuckles] ...to be sure.

382
00:18:59.747 --> 00:19:01.009
Gunderson liked his fishing.

383
00:19:01.183 --> 00:19:03.403
He had a fishing rod in his one hand

384
00:19:03.577 --> 00:19:07.102
and a auger in the other. so my guess.

385
00:19:07.537 --> 00:19:09.452
man thought he was going ice fishing.

386
00:19:09.974 --> 00:19:12.194
At night. in his underwear?

387
00:19:12.368 --> 00:19:16.067
[chuckles] Well. as you can see. the man was a drinker.

388
00:19:16.633 --> 00:19:18.200
Kibner: And a son of a bitch.

389
00:19:18.374 --> 00:19:20.768
but then again. he was our son of a bitch. right?

390
00:19:20.942 --> 00:19:22.639
- [laughs]
- Hey. Doc. Give me a minute.

391
00:19:22.813 --> 00:19:24.250
I'd like to bend his ear. okay?

392
00:19:25.076 --> 00:19:26.817
Now. Yeah. Thank you.

393
00:19:26.991 --> 00:19:28.863
I want to thank you for coming.

394
00:19:29.255 --> 00:19:30.256
Of course.

395
00:19:30.778 --> 00:19:32.214
So. let me get this straight.

396
00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:33.911
Did I hear...

397
00:19:36.436 --> 00:19:38.394
you saw the moose?

398
00:19:38.568 --> 00:19:40.570
I did. I got a picture of it.

399
00:19:40.744 --> 00:19:42.224
Kibner: God damn!

400
00:19:42.398 --> 00:19:44.159
I am the only one in this town who has never seen

401
00:19:44.183 --> 00:19:45.314
that fucking moose.

402
00:19:45.662 --> 00:19:47.621
and I keep an eye out for it.

403
00:19:48.187 --> 00:19:49.971
You know. in Native American culture.

404
00:19:50.145 --> 00:19:54.105
the moose is a symbol of endurance and survival. Hmm?

405
00:19:55.455 --> 00:19:56.456
- I...
- Kibner: So.

406
00:19:57.631 --> 00:19:59.285
what do you think of our little town?

407
00:20:00.329 --> 00:20:03.506
- It's. um. charming.
- Yeah. You know. I hear

408
00:20:03.680 --> 00:20:06.466
that you are a very laid-back kind of guy.

409
00:20:06.988 --> 00:20:09.033
not a crack-the-whip sort.

410
00:20:09.817 --> 00:20:11.217
Well. I mean. I've been known to...

411
00:20:11.384 --> 00:20:12.950
Did you ever think about settling down?

412
00:20:14.561 --> 00:20:17.520
You could be a real sheriff for more than a few weeks.

413
00:20:18.391 --> 00:20:20.436
You could build a whole new life here in Normal.

414
00:20:21.045 --> 00:20:25.049
because we really celebrate the community.

415
00:20:25.224 --> 00:20:29.140
Around here. it's always one for all.

416
00:20:29.315 --> 00:20:30.533
- That sounds...
- Mayor?

417
00:20:30.707 --> 00:20:31.534
- Kibner: Yeah?
- It's time.

418
00:20:31.708 --> 00:20:32.927
Kibner: Yeah.

419
00:20:33.101 --> 00:20:34.537
But I want you to think about it.

420
00:20:34.711 --> 00:20:35.930
- I will.
- Kibner: All right.

421
00:20:40.543 --> 00:20:42.502
Alex: What do you mean. get out?

422
00:20:42.676 --> 00:20:44.721
- Why is that of your...
- [car horn honking]

423
00:20:44.895 --> 00:20:45.895
Alex: Fine.

424
00:20:47.463 --> 00:20:49.183
Blaine: Have you been sleeping in your van?

425
00:20:49.987 --> 00:20:51.337
What? What?

426
00:20:51.511 --> 00:20:52.773
Blaine: You're a mess.

427
00:20:54.209 --> 00:20:56.037
You're not the sheriff yet. Blaine!

428
00:20:57.560 --> 00:20:58.692
Mike: Hey. boss.

429
00:21:00.084 --> 00:21:01.695
I was just. uh. checking on you.

430
00:21:01.869 --> 00:21:05.220
- Uh... you good?
- I'm fine.

431
00:21:05.394 --> 00:21:07.514
Well. I just wanted to let you know that they put out

432
00:21:07.614 --> 00:21:09.920
more of those mini egg rolls. They're custom.

433
00:21:10.747 --> 00:21:12.532
And the mayor's just about to tell the story

434
00:21:12.706 --> 00:21:14.838
about the time he went on the cruise with Jane Fonda.

435
00:21:15.012 --> 00:21:17.276
- so...
- [engine revving]

436
00:21:18.886 --> 00:21:20.975
Ulysses: You know who that is in the van?

437
00:21:21.149 --> 00:21:24.544
Mike: Sheriff Gunderson's. uh. daughter. I think.

438
00:21:25.284 --> 00:21:26.285
Alex.

439
00:21:29.113 --> 00:21:31.072
["Ain't She Sweet" playing]

440
00:21:31.246 --> 00:21:33.030
♪ Here she comes on Down the street ♪

441
00:21:33.204 --> 00:21:34.921
♪ Ain't she sweet with that Style and that smile ♪

442
00:21:34.945 --> 00:21:36.120
♪ And don't you know... ♪

443
00:21:37.557 --> 00:21:39.994
Hey. lawman. Up for a game?

444
00:21:41.082 --> 00:21:44.128
Uh. my hands are shaky. They only trust me with a gun.

445
00:21:44.303 --> 00:21:46.566
[chuckles] Company. then?

446
00:21:46.740 --> 00:21:47.915
♪ That's my girl ♪

447
00:21:48.089 --> 00:21:49.090
I got to warn you.

448
00:21:49.830 --> 00:21:51.092
I'm not very good.

449
00:21:51.745 --> 00:21:53.790
So. would you say you knew Gunderson well?

450
00:21:53.964 --> 00:21:56.315
Gunderson? Yeah. I knew him pretty well.

451
00:21:57.446 --> 00:21:59.448
It was sad. the way he. uh...

452
00:22:01.232 --> 00:22:02.277
you know.

453
00:22:02.799 --> 00:22:04.801
But he liked to drink. He liked to fish.

454
00:22:04.975 --> 00:22:07.151
So the way I see it. he died doing what he loved best.

455
00:22:07.891 --> 00:22:08.892
You fish?

456
00:22:09.284 --> 00:22:11.939
Uh. when I was a kid. with my dad.

457
00:22:12.505 --> 00:22:14.420
- You?
- Me? Fuck no.

458
00:22:15.159 --> 00:22:16.987
Probably the only one in town who don't.

459
00:22:17.205 --> 00:22:20.251
but in the end. death... comes for us all.

460
00:22:20.426 --> 00:22:21.470
don't it. lawman?

461
00:22:22.689 --> 00:22:24.952
I'm not getting a Sheriff out of you. huh?

462
00:22:25.648 --> 00:22:28.434
If you really were. you would. but are you?

463
00:22:31.306 --> 00:22:32.762
- [glasses clink]
- You've been listening

464
00:22:32.786 --> 00:22:35.005
to my internal monologue. haven't you?

465
00:22:35.179 --> 00:22:36.311
That's my job.

466
00:22:38.313 --> 00:22:40.446
I'm Moira. the barkeeper here.

467
00:22:43.666 --> 00:22:44.711
Rack 'em up.

468
00:22:45.538 --> 00:22:46.539
Why are you here?

469
00:22:46.713 --> 00:22:48.628
Stop fucking around. Come on.

470
00:22:49.498 --> 00:22:50.498
I'm all ears.

471
00:22:51.282 --> 00:22:52.327
All right.

472
00:22:54.721 --> 00:22:58.507
I used to be a regular sheriff. Nice county

473
00:22:58.681 --> 00:23:00.640
with a couple little towns just like this one.

474
00:23:00.814 --> 00:23:02.859
I married my high school sweetheart.

475
00:23:04.165 --> 00:23:07.516
- Moira: Perfect.
- It was. I was. uh...

476
00:23:09.300 --> 00:23:10.606
pretty proud of myself.

477
00:23:11.955 --> 00:23:14.871
I walked through life with my head held high.

478
00:23:15.045 --> 00:23:16.351
I knew who I was.

479
00:23:21.574 --> 00:23:23.358
Then this girl. uh...

480
00:23:24.838 --> 00:23:27.014
Her dad. someone I knew.

481
00:23:27.580 --> 00:23:30.234
a. uh. upstanding citizen...

482
00:23:33.150 --> 00:23:34.195
had been. uh...

483
00:23:39.896 --> 00:23:41.376
I didn't believe her.

484
00:23:44.205 --> 00:23:47.382
Short while later. there was an incident at the house.

485
00:23:49.210 --> 00:23:51.604
Gunshots. and I went in.

486
00:23:52.692 --> 00:23:55.216
And she was standing over him.

487
00:23:56.391 --> 00:23:59.220
He was wounded. She had a gun out.

488
00:24:00.395 --> 00:24:04.704
And he was cursing her for what he'd done to her.

489
00:24:06.880 --> 00:24:08.280
And I told her to put the gun down.

490
00:24:08.403 --> 00:24:09.709
and she didn't hesitate.

491
00:24:09.883 --> 00:24:11.841
She shot him right between the eyes.

492
00:24:12.929 --> 00:24:14.583
and then she aimed that gun at me.

493
00:24:15.802 --> 00:24:18.152
And she cursed me for not believing her.

494
00:24:22.286 --> 00:24:23.853
And then we both shot.

495
00:24:26.334 --> 00:24:29.424
Um. I had better aim.

496
00:24:33.254 --> 00:24:34.385
After that...

497
00:24:37.476 --> 00:24:39.216
I got dark inside. and...

498
00:24:42.959 --> 00:24:45.571
I didn't know who I was anymore. and I still don't.

499
00:24:50.967 --> 00:24:52.012
And the wife?

500
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:55.842
I. uh... I was hard to be around.

501
00:24:57.278 --> 00:24:58.497
I still call her.

502
00:25:01.630 --> 00:25:03.110
She doesn't answer. but...

503
00:25:04.415 --> 00:25:05.504
I don't mind.

504
00:25:06.940 --> 00:25:09.246
I live in hope one day she will.

505
00:25:17.951 --> 00:25:19.256
[gun firing]

506
00:25:19.430 --> 00:25:20.780
[pants]

507
00:25:22.956 --> 00:25:24.476
Automated voice: You have one message.

508
00:25:24.610 --> 00:25:25.610
[beeping]

509
00:25:27.482 --> 00:25:29.484
Kibner: Hey. Sheriff. It's the mayor.

510
00:25:29.658 --> 00:25:31.138
- [banging]
- People are really

511
00:25:31.312 --> 00:25:32.768
- liking your light touch.
- [woman groaning]

512
00:25:32.792 --> 00:25:34.054
Have you considered my offer?

513
00:25:34.228 --> 00:25:35.553
Get back to me as soon as you can.

514
00:25:35.577 --> 00:25:36.709
- Come on!
- [beeping]

515
00:25:36.883 --> 00:25:39.320
I want a stupid bun. God damn it.

516
00:25:39.494 --> 00:25:40.930
I bet I can help you with that!

517
00:25:41.278 --> 00:25:42.976
Oh. Hi. Officer.

518
00:25:43.150 --> 00:25:44.543
- Hey.
- I mean Sheriff. I...

519
00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:46.936
- Got stuck.
- Yeah. I see.

520
00:25:47.110 --> 00:25:48.459
Yeah.

521
00:25:48.634 --> 00:25:49.959
Ulysses: Which you think will knock it down.

522
00:25:49.983 --> 00:25:51.419
the caramel or the cookie?

523
00:25:51.593 --> 00:25:53.421
Lori: Uh. I guess the caramel should do it.

524
00:25:53.595 --> 00:25:55.035
Ulysses: Yeah. That's my guess. too.

525
00:25:55.162 --> 00:25:57.512
[people speaking indistinctly]

526
00:25:57.686 --> 00:26:00.080
- What's your dog's name?
- Oh. her name's Olive.

527
00:26:01.168 --> 00:26:02.386
- Nice!
- Yeah!

528
00:26:02.778 --> 00:26:04.301
- Hey. Olive.
- [Olive barking]

529
00:26:04.475 --> 00:26:05.694
What a good dog.

530
00:26:06.173 --> 00:26:07.478
My name's Ulysses.

531
00:26:08.305 --> 00:26:09.393
I'm Lori.

532
00:26:11.221 --> 00:26:12.941
You know. I wish these things had dog food.

533
00:26:15.138 --> 00:26:17.488
- Yeah. Well. someday.
- Yeah.

534
00:26:18.359 --> 00:26:21.101
All right. Well. uh. watch out for the moose.

535
00:26:21.884 --> 00:26:24.713
- Lori: Moose?
- Yeah. Big.

536
00:26:25.192 --> 00:26:26.976
Be careful. He might try and paint you.

537
00:26:27.716 --> 00:26:28.716
Moose?

538
00:26:41.469 --> 00:26:43.427
- [knocking at door]
- Yeah?

539
00:26:44.428 --> 00:26:47.214
- [phone ringing outside]
- [chuckles]

540
00:26:47.388 --> 00:26:49.999
[woman on radio speaking indistinctly]

541
00:26:50.173 --> 00:26:51.173
Ulysses: Thanks.

542
00:26:52.219 --> 00:26:53.612
Look. I...

543
00:26:55.439 --> 00:26:57.050
I don't know if I should say this.

544
00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:01.837
But our mustaches are so similar.

545
00:27:03.447 --> 00:27:05.058
We're like a couple brothers.

546
00:27:06.102 --> 00:27:07.408
Or at least a couple uncles.

547
00:27:08.235 --> 00:27:10.150
[phone ringing]

548
00:27:11.455 --> 00:27:13.893
Well. I should probably get back at it. so...

549
00:27:16.765 --> 00:27:19.550
["Ain't Nobody's Business What
I Do" by Davy Graham playing]

550
00:27:26.253 --> 00:27:28.734
♪ Since you left me. baby ♪

551
00:27:28.908 --> 00:27:29.952
♪ I'm out all night... ♪

552
00:27:30.126 --> 00:27:32.085
Ulysses: How can love go away?

553
00:27:32.259 --> 00:27:34.217
I mean. did I take it for granted?

554
00:27:34.391 --> 00:27:35.610
I guess I did.

555
00:27:36.089 --> 00:27:37.917
I didn't protect that girl.

556
00:27:38.091 --> 00:27:39.832
and I lost you in the bargain.

557
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:44.010
You said I shut down. Penny. You were right.

558
00:27:46.795 --> 00:27:48.231
[siren squeals]

559
00:27:48.405 --> 00:27:49.929
Is this what happened to Gunderson?

560
00:27:50.538 --> 00:27:53.062
Did he give up and say. "Fuck it."

561
00:27:53.628 --> 00:27:55.456
walk into the snow buck naked?

562
00:27:56.718 --> 00:27:58.589
Oh. that's a hell of a way to die.

563
00:28:00.809 --> 00:28:02.637
Alex: I'm not doing anything wrong.

564
00:28:03.769 --> 00:28:04.770
You been drinking?

565
00:28:07.860 --> 00:28:10.645
Not when I was driving. I pulled off to start.

566
00:28:12.952 --> 00:28:14.605
[sniffs] Bourbon?

567
00:28:19.175 --> 00:28:22.265
- That's very impressive.
- You mind if I join you?

568
00:28:23.484 --> 00:28:24.920
I'd... Joi...

569
00:28:29.882 --> 00:28:30.970
[Alex groans]

570
00:28:36.845 --> 00:28:38.238
That's a cool belt.

571
00:28:41.328 --> 00:28:42.329
I'm Alex.

572
00:28:42.982 --> 00:28:44.113
Ulysses: I'm Ulysses.

573
00:28:45.158 --> 00:28:47.160
Can I have the cheap booze?

574
00:28:52.165 --> 00:28:53.993
You're Gunderson's daughter. right?

575
00:28:56.822 --> 00:28:57.822
No.

576
00:28:58.867 --> 00:28:59.868
Oh.

577
00:29:01.174 --> 00:29:04.568
Yeah. Okay. Um. you're... you're Gunderson's kid.

578
00:29:05.395 --> 00:29:08.485
He had lots of pictures of you on the wall in his office.

579
00:29:09.138 --> 00:29:10.139
You got his eyes.

580
00:29:11.837 --> 00:29:14.796
Yeah. Those are old pictures.

581
00:29:17.016 --> 00:29:18.321
He's very proud of me.

582
00:29:19.453 --> 00:29:21.716
Daddy's little girl going military.

583
00:29:22.325 --> 00:29:24.284
Couldn't keep that up. [Chuckles]

584
00:29:26.852 --> 00:29:28.114
You were having an argument

585
00:29:28.288 --> 00:29:29.898
with Deputy Blaine outside the house.

586
00:29:30.072 --> 00:29:31.160
What was that about?

587
00:29:32.466 --> 00:29:34.076
The mayor.

588
00:29:34.250 --> 00:29:37.950
Uh. he didn't want me to attend the memorial service.

589
00:29:38.124 --> 00:29:43.694
because he said that I would be too much of a distraction.

590
00:29:44.913 --> 00:29:48.177
- Well. fuck the mayor.
- Alex: [chuckles] Yeah.

591
00:29:48.351 --> 00:29:50.049
This town used to know right from wrong

592
00:29:50.223 --> 00:29:52.399
before Mayor Kibner got here and...

593
00:29:53.574 --> 00:29:54.774
Tried to make my dad see that.

594
00:29:54.923 --> 00:29:57.926
but he was stuck between me and the town.

595
00:30:00.929 --> 00:30:02.801
And then I made him choose. and...

596
00:30:08.719 --> 00:30:09.719
It killed him.

597
00:30:11.113 --> 00:30:12.854
And I don't know what to do.

598
00:30:15.465 --> 00:30:16.553
Neither do I.

599
00:30:18.294 --> 00:30:20.253
But I got an idea where we could start.

600
00:30:20.427 --> 00:30:22.037
You want to give me that?

601
00:30:30.785 --> 00:30:32.047
Did you catch that?

602
00:30:33.092 --> 00:30:35.050
Yeah. It's my one trick.

603
00:30:38.837 --> 00:30:40.142
How long you been awake?

604
00:30:40.839 --> 00:30:42.101
That's a great question.

605
00:30:43.624 --> 00:30:44.930
I got a place you can crash.

606
00:30:45.756 --> 00:30:46.975
It's a safe place.

607
00:30:48.063 --> 00:30:50.239
It's the safest place in town.

608
00:30:58.117 --> 00:31:00.510
- Alex: This?
- Ulysses: Yeah.

609
00:31:00.684 --> 00:31:03.078
Alex: Hilarious. [Chuckles]

610
00:31:03.252 --> 00:31:04.601
Ulysses: Breakfast is included.

611
00:31:06.168 --> 00:31:07.604
Can I get you anything else?

612
00:31:09.432 --> 00:31:10.477
Lock the door.

613
00:31:13.132 --> 00:31:14.132
Sure.

614
00:31:18.833 --> 00:31:21.183
I'll be in my office. Just yell.

615
00:31:22.054 --> 00:31:23.446
I'll either be sleeping or...

616
00:31:24.708 --> 00:31:25.840
drinking.

617
00:31:27.146 --> 00:31:28.147
Goodnight.

618
00:31:29.322 --> 00:31:31.324
[footsteps receding]

619
00:31:31.498 --> 00:31:32.823
["Trouble" by Connie Converse playing]

620
00:31:32.847 --> 00:31:34.109
♪ Ever since we met... ♪

621
00:31:34.283 --> 00:31:35.608
Lori: It's gonna run like clockwork.

622
00:31:35.632 --> 00:31:36.895
[sighs]

623
00:31:37.504 --> 00:31:38.592
Hey.

624
00:31:39.898 --> 00:31:41.856
- You okay?
- Yeah.

625
00:31:42.030 --> 00:31:43.510
♪ If you go away ♪

626
00:31:43.684 --> 00:31:46.165
♪ As trouble ought to do ♪

627
00:31:46.339 --> 00:31:48.341
♪ Where will I find Another soul ♪

628
00:31:48.515 --> 00:31:51.822
♪ To tell my trouble to? ♪

629
00:31:55.522 --> 00:31:58.351
♪ Then my bed is made of stone ♪

630
00:31:58.525 --> 00:32:01.702
♪ A star has burned my eye ♪

631
00:32:01.876 --> 00:32:04.139
Ulysses: Good morning. food enthusiasts.

632
00:32:04.313 --> 00:32:06.489
♪ And teach her how to cry ♪

633
00:32:06.663 --> 00:32:08.622
♪ But if you go away ♪

634
00:32:08.796 --> 00:32:11.233
♪ As trouble ought to do ♪

635
00:32:11.407 --> 00:32:13.540
♪ Where will I find Another soul ♪

636
00:32:13.714 --> 00:32:16.847
♪ To tell my trouble to? ♪

637
00:32:17.022 --> 00:32:18.501
Second Street right here.

638
00:32:18.675 --> 00:32:20.416
we cannot block that off

639
00:32:20.590 --> 00:32:24.029
because what if Mr. Neville has
some sort of a terrible fall

640
00:32:24.203 --> 00:32:25.726
down here at his house

641
00:32:25.900 --> 00:32:28.076
and then Mrs. Neville gets him into the vehicle...

642
00:32:28.250 --> 00:32:30.296
What? How? No. no. She's a tiny little thing.

643
00:32:30.470 --> 00:32:32.143
- How is she gonna...
- Mike: I don't know.

644
00:32:32.167 --> 00:32:34.735
Maybe they have a dolly or a wheelbarrow or something.

645
00:32:35.214 --> 00:32:38.086
Uh. boss. do you wanna describe

646
00:32:38.260 --> 00:32:40.325
standard operating procedure to the civilian for me?

647
00:32:40.349 --> 00:32:43.526
Well. it's an emergency situation?

648
00:32:43.700 --> 00:32:44.919
It's an emergency.

649
00:32:45.093 --> 00:32:47.835
I'm with Sally. Just move the cones.

650
00:32:48.009 --> 00:32:50.229
Mike: Have we lost all respect for cones?

651
00:32:50.403 --> 00:32:52.492
[alarm blaring]

652
00:32:53.101 --> 00:32:55.538
Ulysses: The hell is that? Is that a test?

653
00:32:56.975 --> 00:32:57.801
Shit.

654
00:32:57.976 --> 00:33:00.979
[alarm continuing]

655
00:33:06.593 --> 00:33:07.874
- [clicking]
- [alarm shutting off]

656
00:33:07.898 --> 00:33:08.898
[sighs]

657
00:33:09.813 --> 00:33:11.772
Oh. shit. Oh.

658
00:33:13.643 --> 00:33:15.254
Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.

659
00:33:15.428 --> 00:33:16.588
- Right behind you.
- Come on!

660
00:33:16.646 --> 00:33:17.691
Okay then.

661
00:33:17.865 --> 00:33:19.127
- [racking gun]
- [screaming]

662
00:33:19.301 --> 00:33:21.129
Lori: Everybody. down and stay down!

663
00:33:21.303 --> 00:33:23.020
- Keith: Guns. kick 'em to me!
- Lori: Nobody move!

664
00:33:23.044 --> 00:33:25.438
Keith: Come on! Kick 'em to me!

665
00:33:25.612 --> 00:33:28.093
Okay. Shit.

666
00:33:28.615 --> 00:33:30.138
All right. babe! All clear!

667
00:33:30.312 --> 00:33:31.792
- Lori: You!
- Keith: Just stay down.

668
00:33:31.966 --> 00:33:34.577
Lori: Fill them! Fill them! Fill them! Fill 'em!

669
00:33:34.751 --> 00:33:35.926
In the bags!

670
00:33:36.579 --> 00:33:38.190
Do what we say and no one gets hurt!

671
00:33:38.364 --> 00:33:39.558
Keith: Everything's going to be okay.

672
00:33:39.582 --> 00:33:40.975
Lori: Come on! Come on! Come on!

673
00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:43.891
Where... Where is the rest of it? This is it?

674
00:33:44.065 --> 00:33:45.936
Sorry. Nobody uses cash anymore.

675
00:33:46.894 --> 00:33:48.374
Lori: Babe. this is. like. two grand.

676
00:33:48.504 --> 00:33:49.549
Keith: Fuck.

677
00:33:51.116 --> 00:33:52.441
- Lori: That's not enough.
- Keith: Fuck!

678
00:33:52.465 --> 00:33:53.585
Lori: It's not enough! Fuck!

679
00:33:53.640 --> 00:33:54.945
We did all this for two grand?

680
00:33:55.120 --> 00:33:56.164
Take me to the vault.

681
00:33:56.338 --> 00:33:57.557
Really? The vault? Really?

682
00:33:57.731 --> 00:34:00.342
Yeah. Please. Terry. to the vault.

683
00:34:01.213 --> 00:34:04.520
Lori: Stay right there. Stay right there. Oh. shit.

684
00:34:04.694 --> 00:34:06.629
Keith: Keep your hands where I can goddamn see them!

685
00:34:06.653 --> 00:34:08.046
Lori: Hey. nobody move!

686
00:34:08.698 --> 00:34:10.676
Baby. we don't have the fucking time to go into the vault.

687
00:34:10.700 --> 00:34:12.702
- We have to go.
- Then we make the time.

688
00:34:12.876 --> 00:34:13.940
Then we make the fucking time.

689
00:34:13.964 --> 00:34:17.142
[groans loudly]

690
00:34:17.316 --> 00:34:18.839
Lori: What's wrong with him?

691
00:34:19.187 --> 00:34:21.450
- Hey.
- Lori: Oh. my God. Fuck!

692
00:34:21.624 --> 00:34:22.625
- Sir?
- Man: Help.

693
00:34:23.104 --> 00:34:24.888
- Lori: Don't kick him!
- Are you okay?

694
00:34:25.063 --> 00:34:26.412
Lori: Stop asking questions.

695
00:34:26.586 --> 00:34:27.998
Don't you see he's having a heart attack?

696
00:34:28.022 --> 00:34:29.589
- Help him! Help him!
- Shit!

697
00:34:30.242 --> 00:34:32.026
Lori: You said no one was going to get hurt.

698
00:34:32.200 --> 00:34:33.680
This is not going like clockwork!

699
00:34:33.854 --> 00:34:36.509
- [groans]
- I... I can't open it!

700
00:34:36.683 --> 00:34:38.467
- Lori: Push and twist!
- I'm pushing!

701
00:34:38.641 --> 00:34:40.315
I'm pushing and I'm twisting! I'm pushing and I'm twisting.

702
00:34:40.339 --> 00:34:42.499
Lori: Push and twist! It's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

703
00:34:42.558 --> 00:34:43.733
[groans]

704
00:34:43.907 --> 00:34:46.214
Okay. Okay. Here you go. Here you go.

705
00:34:46.388 --> 00:34:48.347
Lori: Yeah. Come on. There we go.

706
00:34:48.521 --> 00:34:50.871
- [groans]
- Okay. There we go!

707
00:34:51.045 --> 00:34:52.220
Problem solved!

708
00:34:52.394 --> 00:34:53.994
Keith: He's still having a heart attack.

709
00:34:54.135 --> 00:34:55.634
He's stopped breathing! He's stopped breathing. babe!

710
00:34:55.658 --> 00:34:57.312
- Lori: Help him! Help him!
- Keith: Okay!

711
00:34:57.486 --> 00:34:58.792
Lori: Chest compressions!

712
00:34:58.966 --> 00:35:01.055
- It's fine. It's gonna be fine.
- [grunts]

713
00:35:01.229 --> 00:35:03.492
- Come on. Come on.
- [Keith grunting]

714
00:35:03.666 --> 00:35:05.059
- Lori: Nobody move!
- [beeping]

715
00:35:05.233 --> 00:35:07.017
It's gonna be fine.

716
00:35:07.192 --> 00:35:08.758
[phone beeping. vibrating]

717
00:35:08.932 --> 00:35:10.543
[speaking Japanese]

718
00:35:10.717 --> 00:35:13.720
[phone beeping. vibrating]

719
00:35:20.118 --> 00:35:21.118
Come on. Come on.

720
00:35:21.206 --> 00:35:23.730
[Keith grunts]

721
00:35:23.904 --> 00:35:28.691
[phone beeping. vibrating]

722
00:35:29.692 --> 00:35:31.433
Shit.

723
00:35:31.607 --> 00:35:33.107
Blaine on radio: Sheriff. when we get to the bank.

724
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:34.654
you let me and Mike handle things.

725
00:35:34.828 --> 00:35:36.284
Mike on radio: Yeah. You best supervise.

726
00:35:36.308 --> 00:35:37.700
You know. you just hang back...

727
00:35:37.874 --> 00:35:39.025
- [Keith grunts]
- Lori: It's gonna be fine.

728
00:35:39.049 --> 00:35:40.094
Come on.

729
00:35:40.268 --> 00:35:43.837
[screaming]

730
00:35:47.101 --> 00:35:49.451
- [Lori shouting]
- [gun firing]

731
00:35:49.625 --> 00:35:50.625
[screaming]

732
00:35:50.757 --> 00:35:52.411
- [firing]
- [yelping]

733
00:35:52.585 --> 00:35:53.586
- [firing]
- [grunting]

734
00:35:53.760 --> 00:35:55.544
- [firing]
- [screaming]

735
00:35:55.718 --> 00:35:57.416
[groans]

736
00:35:57.590 --> 00:36:00.767
Keith! Oh. my God!

737
00:36:00.941 --> 00:36:02.290
Baby. I'm so sorry!

738
00:36:02.464 --> 00:36:04.771
- Let me see. Let me see.
- You shot me.

739
00:36:04.945 --> 00:36:06.294
It was an accident!

740
00:36:06.468 --> 00:36:08.992
Keith: It's just a nick. The stab wound's worse.

741
00:36:09.167 --> 00:36:10.951
- I'm sorry!
- You killed the other guys.

742
00:36:11.125 --> 00:36:14.172
Yeah. What do I do? What do I do? What do I do?

743
00:36:14.346 --> 00:36:15.346
[grunts]

744
00:36:16.348 --> 00:36:17.784
Keep going.

745
00:36:19.307 --> 00:36:21.875
[sirens wailing]

746
00:36:35.236 --> 00:36:37.282
- [phone ringing]
- Lori: Okay. Right. Come on.

747
00:36:37.456 --> 00:36:39.197
- Excuse me? Miss?
- What?

748
00:36:39.371 --> 00:36:41.982
- Do you want me to get that?
- What?

749
00:36:42.156 --> 00:36:43.592
Terry: The machine will get it.

750
00:36:43.766 --> 00:36:45.812
- Lori: Come on. Come on.
- [phone ringing]

751
00:36:45.986 --> 00:36:47.509
- No one's answering.
- Keep trying!

752
00:36:47.683 --> 00:36:49.603
What's the point? It's all automated now anyway.

753
00:36:49.642 --> 00:36:50.904
[dog barking]

754
00:36:52.166 --> 00:36:53.167
[whining]

755
00:36:56.823 --> 00:36:57.954
What's he doing?

756
00:36:59.217 --> 00:37:00.653
Ulysses: Hey. it's okay. Olive.

757
00:37:00.827 --> 00:37:01.827
Is that a dog?

758
00:37:04.047 --> 00:37:06.049
Mike. cover at the rear.

759
00:37:06.224 --> 00:37:08.182
- Deputy. cover my ass.
- Oh. just hang on.

760
00:37:08.356 --> 00:37:10.837
Guys... I'm going in.

761
00:37:11.011 --> 00:37:12.578
The fuck you are.

762
00:37:14.057 --> 00:37:15.407
- Sir.
- Look.

763
00:37:15.581 --> 00:37:16.645
Let's just wait for some more backup.

764
00:37:16.669 --> 00:37:18.192
If we don't play this right.

765
00:37:18.366 --> 00:37:19.976
we're going to have a massacre in there.

766
00:37:22.109 --> 00:37:24.024
- You guys okay?
- Mike: Yeah.

767
00:37:24.503 --> 00:37:25.503
Calm down.

768
00:37:26.200 --> 00:37:27.201
This is messy.

769
00:37:28.681 --> 00:37:30.335
What are we going to do about him?

770
00:37:31.727 --> 00:37:35.035
- Why you asking me?
- Calm cleans messy.

771
00:37:35.601 --> 00:37:39.605
- I'm going to talk to them.
- [cell phone ringing]

772
00:37:41.911 --> 00:37:43.696
Blaine: We got us a situation.

773
00:37:45.001 --> 00:37:46.612
Yeah. I do know what I signed up for.

774
00:37:46.786 --> 00:37:48.866
but jeez. I didn't think I'd actually have to do it.

775
00:37:49.397 --> 00:37:50.529
Hello?

776
00:37:58.537 --> 00:37:59.538
Fuck.

777
00:38:00.408 --> 00:38:01.408
Deputy. what did he say?

778
00:38:02.105 --> 00:38:03.237
You know what he said.

779
00:38:04.717 --> 00:38:06.371
We all agreed to the same damn thing.

780
00:38:11.289 --> 00:38:12.377
Come on. Come on. Come on.

781
00:38:12.551 --> 00:38:13.911
Ulysses: Stay cool! I'm coming in!

782
00:38:23.257 --> 00:38:24.737
- Lori: You okay?
- [breathes heavily]

783
00:38:25.128 --> 00:38:26.260
Yeah.

784
00:38:30.395 --> 00:38:31.439
Damn it.

785
00:38:37.097 --> 00:38:38.185
- [gun firing]
- Ah!

786
00:38:38.359 --> 00:38:40.927
[gun firing. glass shattering]

787
00:38:42.494 --> 00:38:45.410
- [grunting]
- [hostages screaming]

788
00:38:45.584 --> 00:38:46.802
[coughing]

789
00:38:46.976 --> 00:38:48.302
Mike: Oh. shit. Did you hit his vest?

790
00:38:48.326 --> 00:38:49.370
Fuck.

791
00:38:50.153 --> 00:38:51.546
- [gun firing]
- [shouting]

792
00:38:51.720 --> 00:38:53.520
Hold fire! Hold fire! Hold your fucking fire!

793
00:38:53.592 --> 00:38:54.672
You have someone out there?

794
00:38:54.723 --> 00:38:56.159
Why are they shooting at you?

795
00:38:56.334 --> 00:38:59.293
[guns firing]

796
00:38:59.772 --> 00:39:01.426
- Ah!
- [firing]

797
00:39:01.600 --> 00:39:02.600
Motherfucker!

798
00:39:02.644 --> 00:39:05.255
[firing]

799
00:39:05.430 --> 00:39:06.779
- Ah!
- [firing]

800
00:39:06.953 --> 00:39:08.911
[grunts] Did I get him?

801
00:39:09.085 --> 00:39:10.086
- Uh...
- Did I get him?

802
00:39:10.260 --> 00:39:11.479
Yeah. Yeah. No.

803
00:39:11.653 --> 00:39:14.003
- [gun firing]
- [yelping]

804
00:39:14.177 --> 00:39:15.396
[panting]

805
00:39:17.616 --> 00:39:19.487
Ah! My ear!

806
00:39:19.966 --> 00:39:21.315
- Mike. my ear!
- [groans]

807
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:23.926
- [grunting]
- [clicking]

808
00:39:24.100 --> 00:39:25.275
Get down!

809
00:39:25.450 --> 00:39:26.494
- [firing]
- [shouting]

810
00:39:30.498 --> 00:39:31.498
Fuck!

811
00:39:33.458 --> 00:39:35.982
[Blaine groaning]

812
00:39:36.156 --> 00:39:37.263
- [gun firing]
- [Lori shrieking]

813
00:39:37.287 --> 00:39:38.287
Get behind me!

814
00:39:38.376 --> 00:39:39.464
[firing]

815
00:39:39.638 --> 00:39:40.638
Go! Go! Go!

816
00:39:40.769 --> 00:39:41.944
[clicking]

817
00:39:42.118 --> 00:39:43.118
[firing]

818
00:39:43.206 --> 00:39:43.990
You too! Come on!

819
00:39:44.164 --> 00:39:45.470
[gun firing]

820
00:39:46.775 --> 00:39:49.822
[firing]

821
00:39:49.996 --> 00:39:52.128
[people shouting]

822
00:39:56.350 --> 00:39:58.265
[groaning]

823
00:39:58.439 --> 00:40:00.267
- Ulysses: Move! Move!
- [people shouting]

824
00:40:00.441 --> 00:40:01.462
Man: Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

825
00:40:01.486 --> 00:40:02.487
Stop!

826
00:40:06.012 --> 00:40:07.100
I shot Terry.

827
00:40:08.362 --> 00:40:10.843
It's fine. alright? Just... Just help me with my ear.

828
00:40:11.017 --> 00:40:12.540
You think they can put it back on?

829
00:40:12.714 --> 00:40:14.431
- Okay. Oh. that's bad.
- Blaine: I need more snow.

830
00:40:14.455 --> 00:40:17.371
Mike: Oh. that's bad. Really bad.

831
00:40:17.545 --> 00:40:19.436
Is this some kind of setup? Are you guys in on this?

832
00:40:19.460 --> 00:40:22.028
No! We're just... Shooting at us I get.

833
00:40:22.202 --> 00:40:24.117
It's fair. We're robbing the bank.

834
00:40:24.291 --> 00:40:25.379
But you're the sheriff.

835
00:40:25.553 --> 00:40:26.704
Why are they shooting at you?

836
00:40:26.728 --> 00:40:27.729
I'm at a loss.

837
00:40:27.947 --> 00:40:29.011
Lori: But you're the sheriff!

838
00:40:29.035 --> 00:40:30.428
I'm the goddamn substitute.

839
00:40:30.602 --> 00:40:31.777
- What. man?
- What?

840
00:40:31.951 --> 00:40:33.058
What are you talking about. man?

841
00:40:33.082 --> 00:40:34.388
- Hey!
- Okay!

842
00:40:34.562 --> 00:40:36.259
- I'm sorry!
- What's going on?

843
00:40:38.566 --> 00:40:40.126
Why didn't you guys just take the till?

844
00:40:40.220 --> 00:40:41.719
When you asked about the vault. they... they...

845
00:40:41.743 --> 00:40:43.049
What about the vault?

846
00:40:45.747 --> 00:40:47.488
Don't make me ask twice.

847
00:40:55.365 --> 00:40:57.019
Holy shit.

848
00:41:01.110 --> 00:41:03.852
Yeah. We weren't after this.

849
00:41:04.244 --> 00:41:06.202
- What is this?
- Oh.

850
00:41:06.376 --> 00:41:07.987
Oh. come on.

851
00:41:09.554 --> 00:41:11.120
Hey! Come back here!

852
00:41:11.294 --> 00:41:12.294
Where you going?

853
00:41:13.079 --> 00:41:14.472
Calm the fuck down!

854
00:41:15.777 --> 00:41:17.344
Be cool. man. Just chill. Chill.

855
00:41:17.518 --> 00:41:19.128
Terry: We're beyond chill. mother...

856
00:41:19.302 --> 00:41:20.695
- Ah!
- [gun firing]

857
00:41:20.869 --> 00:41:21.870
[thudding]

858
00:41:22.044 --> 00:41:23.089
Oh.

859
00:41:25.091 --> 00:41:29.574
[panting]

860
00:41:31.271 --> 00:41:33.229
[knocking]

861
00:41:36.624 --> 00:41:37.949
Lori: Okay. We gotta put pressure on it.

862
00:41:37.973 --> 00:41:39.497
Ready? One. two. three.

863
00:41:39.671 --> 00:41:41.499
- [groaning] Oh. yeah.
- I know. I'm sorry.

864
00:41:41.673 --> 00:41:42.500
That stings.

865
00:41:42.674 --> 00:41:45.241
[knocking]

866
00:41:45.415 --> 00:41:46.504
[groaning]

867
00:41:46.678 --> 00:41:49.245
[knocking]

868
00:41:53.815 --> 00:41:55.295
[gun firing]

869
00:41:55.469 --> 00:41:56.469
[yelping]

870
00:41:56.601 --> 00:41:57.950
[shouting] Mike. is that you?

871
00:41:58.124 --> 00:41:59.342
I can hear your jacket!

872
00:41:59.517 --> 00:42:00.518
No. boss!

873
00:42:02.781 --> 00:42:05.131
- [firing]
- [grunting]

874
00:42:05.305 --> 00:42:06.480
[gun firing]

875
00:42:09.004 --> 00:42:10.005
Go around!

876
00:42:10.528 --> 00:42:12.530
Please. get us out of here.

877
00:42:13.792 --> 00:42:15.271
Oh.

878
00:42:15.445 --> 00:42:16.945
- What's happening?
- Ulysses: Heck if I know.

879
00:42:16.969 --> 00:42:18.274
It's Lori. right?

880
00:42:18.448 --> 00:42:20.015
Yeah. This is Keith.

881
00:42:20.189 --> 00:42:21.321
That's Ulysses.

882
00:42:22.191 --> 00:42:25.543
Oh. hey. Did you ever get dog food for Olive?

883
00:42:25.717 --> 00:42:27.849
- Yeah. I did.
- Ulysses: Good.

884
00:42:28.023 --> 00:42:29.329
What is going on here?

885
00:42:29.982 --> 00:42:31.679
I don't know what the hell this is.

886
00:42:32.550 --> 00:42:36.075
but they shot at me and you didn't.

887
00:42:36.249 --> 00:42:39.034
so the way I see it. this fucked-up little trio of ours.

888
00:42:39.208 --> 00:42:40.862
we're a team. You good with that?

889
00:42:41.036 --> 00:42:42.081
Lori: Yes. sir.

890
00:42:44.126 --> 00:42:45.126
Yes. sir.

891
00:42:46.564 --> 00:42:47.695
How you feeling?

892
00:42:48.043 --> 00:42:49.828
Yeah. about as good as I look.

893
00:42:50.002 --> 00:42:51.830
So worse than I thought. then.

894
00:42:52.700 --> 00:42:54.659
[phone ringing]

895
00:42:54.833 --> 00:42:56.661
I'll buy us some time.

896
00:42:57.313 --> 00:42:58.445
Time for what?

897
00:42:59.315 --> 00:43:00.316
I'm working on that.

898
00:43:01.143 --> 00:43:02.492
See what's inside those crates.

899
00:43:03.711 --> 00:43:06.845
- Why?
- Because they look military.

900
00:43:07.019 --> 00:43:08.368
and we look outgunned.

901
00:43:10.326 --> 00:43:13.025
[groaning]

902
00:43:16.550 --> 00:43:18.465
Deputy Blaine? You still with us?

903
00:43:18.639 --> 00:43:20.772
Kibner: Yeah. Luckily for you. he is.

904
00:43:21.381 --> 00:43:23.688
You managed to shoot his ear off. I'll tell you.

905
00:43:23.862 --> 00:43:24.906
Mayor.

906
00:43:25.080 --> 00:43:26.560
Kibner: Yeah. Sheriff...

907
00:43:27.996 --> 00:43:28.997
Sheriff?

908
00:43:30.520 --> 00:43:31.565
He hung up on me.

909
00:43:32.348 --> 00:43:33.698
The fucker hung up on me.

910
00:43:34.742 --> 00:43:36.309
No. no. no. Lower your guns.

911
00:43:36.483 --> 00:43:38.703
My bad. My bad. Bars.

912
00:43:40.226 --> 00:43:41.746
All right. Here. I got him. I got him.

913
00:43:41.793 --> 00:43:42.793
You were saying?

914
00:43:42.924 --> 00:43:44.404
Kibner: Yeah. I was saying

915
00:43:44.578 --> 00:43:48.408
that I asked my deputy to shoot you clean through.

916
00:43:48.582 --> 00:43:52.238
but I guess. like. a small request is too much for him.

917
00:43:52.412 --> 00:43:54.414
What are you. blind?

918
00:43:54.588 --> 00:43:56.242
Blaine: Sorry. Snow got into my eye.

919
00:43:56.416 --> 00:43:58.244
so I had to close it and... and...

920
00:43:58.418 --> 00:43:59.506
Kibner: You what?

921
00:43:59.680 --> 00:44:01.029
I've seen what's in the vault.

922
00:44:01.203 --> 00:44:03.466
- [banging]
- Who's in on this?

923
00:44:03.641 --> 00:44:06.034
Is it you and Blaine or the whole department?

924
00:44:07.079 --> 00:44:11.257
Son. I have got the whole town at my back.

925
00:44:12.650 --> 00:44:15.783
Let me explain. You're just one cop.

926
00:44:15.957 --> 00:44:20.048
We're Normal. population 1.890.

927
00:44:24.400 --> 00:44:25.793
What's it all about. Mayor?

928
00:44:26.620 --> 00:44:28.274
Kibner: What's this all about?

929
00:44:30.145 --> 00:44:31.799
You know. main streets like ours...

930
00:44:33.366 --> 00:44:36.761
they are like strewn corpses across America.

931
00:44:36.935 --> 00:44:39.024
holding on by a thread.

932
00:44:39.198 --> 00:44:42.114
hoping they can keep a dialysis center open

933
00:44:42.288 --> 00:44:43.768
or a little thrift shop

934
00:44:43.942 --> 00:44:46.858
or an antique store with no antiques.

935
00:44:47.032 --> 00:44:49.991
They've been plundered by banks and conglomerates.

936
00:44:50.165 --> 00:44:52.254
So when the Yakuza came

937
00:44:52.428 --> 00:44:53.797
and said they want to make a deal...

938
00:44:53.821 --> 00:44:55.518
With the Yakuza?

939
00:44:55.693 --> 00:44:56.824
Kibner: Trust me.

940
00:44:56.998 --> 00:44:58.434
They're a thing.

941
00:44:58.608 --> 00:45:00.523
They make a lot of money in America.

942
00:45:00.698 --> 00:45:02.308
They can't ship it all home.

943
00:45:02.482 --> 00:45:03.962
So when they asked us to hold

944
00:45:04.136 --> 00:45:06.094
a portion of their illicit US profits...

945
00:45:06.268 --> 00:45:07.835
for a percentage. mind...

946
00:45:08.009 --> 00:45:10.272
I said. "Sure. We'll take it."

947
00:45:10.446 --> 00:45:12.622
And the whole town sold its soul.

948
00:45:12.797 --> 00:45:14.189
Not the whole town.

949
00:45:14.363 --> 00:45:16.714
There was some negative Nancys.

950
00:45:17.802 --> 00:45:20.979
But I took care of them. trust me.

951
00:45:22.981 --> 00:45:24.373
Ulysses: And. uh...

952
00:45:24.547 --> 00:45:26.767
me having seen what I've seen.

953
00:45:26.941 --> 00:45:29.509
I guess there's no way out of this for me alive.

954
00:45:29.683 --> 00:45:32.512
You know. there's a way. You want a deal?

955
00:45:32.686 --> 00:45:34.732
Ulysses: What kind of deal?

956
00:45:34.906 --> 00:45:37.865
You put a bullet in the head of those two assholes

957
00:45:38.039 --> 00:45:39.693
that started this trouble.

958
00:45:40.563 --> 00:45:41.739
the blood on your hands

959
00:45:41.913 --> 00:45:43.828
is insurance enough for me.

960
00:45:44.437 --> 00:45:45.960
What do you say?

961
00:45:54.229 --> 00:45:55.840
All right. now. he hung up on me.

962
00:45:56.014 --> 00:45:58.886
Now. he hung up on me! Guns up!

963
00:45:59.060 --> 00:46:00.845
Officer: All right. here we go. here we go.

964
00:46:03.195 --> 00:46:04.239
What'd you find?

965
00:46:04.413 --> 00:46:05.719
[moose grunting]

966
00:46:05.893 --> 00:46:07.293
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

967
00:46:08.026 --> 00:46:10.550
- There it is.
- [moose bellowing]

968
00:46:11.377 --> 00:46:12.900
[grunting]

969
00:46:13.074 --> 00:46:14.684
It's so beautiful.

970
00:46:14.859 --> 00:46:16.208
[electricity buzzing]

971
00:46:16.382 --> 00:46:18.950
Man: There goes the substation at Brandon!

972
00:46:19.124 --> 00:46:21.561
Storm must have knocked the power out.

973
00:46:21.735 --> 00:46:23.215
Oh. darn.

974
00:46:25.695 --> 00:46:26.827
Alex: Hello?

975
00:46:27.697 --> 00:46:28.873
Let me out!

976
00:46:37.577 --> 00:46:39.337
Officer: I think this is a good omen. right?

977
00:46:40.580 --> 00:46:42.234
[police officers yelping]

978
00:46:44.976 --> 00:46:47.935
- Jesus.
- That's not where I was aiming.

979
00:46:48.457 --> 00:46:50.198
- [tense music playing]
- Let's go.

980
00:46:51.286 --> 00:46:52.810
I think I can see someone.

981
00:46:54.768 --> 00:46:56.204
[police officers screaming]

982
00:46:57.379 --> 00:46:59.555
[screaming]

983
00:47:01.253 --> 00:47:02.515
[screams]

984
00:47:08.260 --> 00:47:11.741
[screaming. shouting]

985
00:47:11.916 --> 00:47:13.091
Give me that.

986
00:47:22.491 --> 00:47:23.797
[music concludes]

987
00:47:25.320 --> 00:47:26.887
[Mike breathes heavily]

988
00:47:27.061 --> 00:47:29.237
- Police officer: Holy shit!
- Fuck this!

989
00:47:30.282 --> 00:47:31.718
Fuck this town!

990
00:47:31.892 --> 00:47:33.720
- Blaine: Calm down. Tom.
- I am outta here!

991
00:47:33.894 --> 00:47:35.374
- [gun firing]
- [groans]

992
00:47:38.203 --> 00:47:40.988
- Anyone else?
- Blaine: No. no. no. no.

993
00:47:41.989 --> 00:47:43.429
We're all good. Joe. We're all good.

994
00:47:44.209 --> 00:47:46.689
- Where did they go?
- Oh. hey. Mr. Joe.

995
00:47:46.864 --> 00:47:48.300
Where did they go?

996
00:47:48.474 --> 00:47:50.302
They headed down. back towards Main Street.

997
00:47:51.346 --> 00:47:52.826
You touch the base with Oyabun?

998
00:47:53.696 --> 00:47:54.828
Which means?

999
00:47:55.307 --> 00:47:57.004
There's no way to get a hold of him.

1000
00:47:57.178 --> 00:48:00.834
For all he knows. his piggy bank was raided.

1001
00:48:01.313 --> 00:48:03.141
Oyabun is coming.

1002
00:48:05.665 --> 00:48:06.709
[in Japanese] No answer.

1003
00:48:07.536 --> 00:48:08.973
What the fuck?

1004
00:48:10.670 --> 00:48:13.238
Okay. you sons of bitches! We fly tonight!

1005
00:48:15.153 --> 00:48:17.938
[wind gusting]

1006
00:48:20.158 --> 00:48:21.333
Ulysses: [in English] Go! Go!

1007
00:48:23.944 --> 00:48:26.338
Shit. I'm out. Get off the street.

1008
00:48:26.512 --> 00:48:28.209
We're sitting ducks out here. Keep moving.

1009
00:48:28.383 --> 00:48:30.429
- Hey. freeze!
- Ulysses: Oh. shit!

1010
00:48:31.865 --> 00:48:34.041
Oh. I'm good. I'm good. I'm good. I'm just...

1011
00:48:34.215 --> 00:48:35.913
Ulysses: Get inside! Get inside!

1012
00:48:36.087 --> 00:48:37.958
- Officer: Drop it now!
- Ulysses: Don't shoot!

1013
00:48:39.873 --> 00:48:41.919
Stand down! [Grunts]

1014
00:48:43.094 --> 00:48:44.747
Keith: Oh! Okay!

1015
00:48:44.922 --> 00:48:46.706
- Oh. God! [Groans]
- Come on. baby.

1016
00:48:46.880 --> 00:48:48.838
I thought this was a normal town.

1017
00:48:49.013 --> 00:48:50.188
but this is not normal.

1018
00:48:52.233 --> 00:48:53.713
Ulysses: Stop shooting!

1019
00:48:54.932 --> 00:48:57.021
- God damn it!
- [ambient music playing]

1020
00:48:57.195 --> 00:48:58.544
Lori: Are both your wounds okay?

1021
00:48:58.718 --> 00:49:00.154
- Yeah.
- [door clanking]

1022
00:49:00.328 --> 00:49:03.201
I think I heard something. Hold on. Hold on.

1023
00:49:04.332 --> 00:49:05.333
Come on.

1024
00:49:09.511 --> 00:49:10.511
Hello?

1025
00:49:12.253 --> 00:49:14.516
- [shop bell jangling]
- How is he?

1026
00:49:14.690 --> 00:49:17.041
Not good. I think there's someone in here.

1027
00:49:17.215 --> 00:49:18.259
Mary Beth: Hello?

1028
00:49:19.304 --> 00:49:20.759
- Ulysses: Mary Beth.
- Oh. my God. What happened?

1029
00:49:20.783 --> 00:49:22.394
Have you got a first-aid kit?

1030
00:49:22.568 --> 00:49:24.111
- Yeah. in my stock room.
- [radio static crackles]

1031
00:49:24.135 --> 00:49:26.702
Is that radio working? How is that on?

1032
00:49:26.876 --> 00:49:28.530
Uh. battery operated.

1033
00:49:28.704 --> 00:49:30.924
You said this is a CB radio. too. right?

1034
00:49:31.098 --> 00:49:32.404
Where's the mic on this thing?

1035
00:49:32.578 --> 00:49:34.101
Mike: Hey. Knitting Needle.

1036
00:49:34.275 --> 00:49:36.234
if you see the sheriff. you stop him. He knows.

1037
00:49:36.408 --> 00:49:37.975
Shit! [Grunts]

1038
00:49:42.414 --> 00:49:45.417
- [wind gusting]
- [grunts]

1039
00:49:48.986 --> 00:49:50.596
Ulysses: Calm down. Mary Beth!

1040
00:49:52.424 --> 00:49:54.034
We don't wanna hurt you!

1041
00:49:54.208 --> 00:49:58.256
Mary Beth: Sure. you don't. I wasn't born yesterday!

1042
00:50:10.094 --> 00:50:11.747
[bullets ricocheting]

1043
00:50:13.793 --> 00:50:16.187
[bullets ricocheting]

1044
00:50:16.361 --> 00:50:20.800
Mary Beth: Oh. no. my shop! Goddamn tourists.

1045
00:50:21.496 --> 00:50:24.543
Ain't got no fucking respect.

1046
00:50:25.761 --> 00:50:26.849
Okay.

1047
00:50:28.938 --> 00:50:30.940
[strains]

1048
00:50:33.073 --> 00:50:35.989
- [screams. gasps]
- [gun clicking]

1049
00:50:36.468 --> 00:50:37.991
- Ha!
- Ulysses: Hey. Mary Beth!

1050
00:50:40.646 --> 00:50:42.648
[screams. grunts]

1051
00:50:42.822 --> 00:50:46.130
Let me go. you fucker! [Groans]

1052
00:50:50.047 --> 00:50:51.483
Suck on this!

1053
00:50:54.834 --> 00:50:58.055
[gurgling]

1054
00:50:59.012 --> 00:51:01.580
Lori: Oh. God. Sorry. lady.

1055
00:51:09.022 --> 00:51:10.328
[gasps]

1056
00:51:12.678 --> 00:51:14.395
- Kenny: Let there be light.
- [music concludes]

1057
00:51:14.419 --> 00:51:17.770
- [power whirring]
- ['50s blues rock playing]

1058
00:51:17.944 --> 00:51:22.557
Joe: You don't understand. Oyabun will have us all killed.

1059
00:51:22.731 --> 00:51:25.647
Blaine: Kenny will help us out.
We'll get nice and warm inside.

1060
00:51:25.821 --> 00:51:28.694
Come on! Regroup and rearm.

1061
00:51:32.219 --> 00:51:33.786
♪ Mm. mm. mm-hmm ♪

1062
00:51:35.048 --> 00:51:36.571
Dr. Velie: In here. Deputy Blaine.

1063
00:51:36.745 --> 00:51:38.399
[shivers]

1064
00:51:38.573 --> 00:51:40.116
- Kenny: Evening. everybody.
- Blaine: Oh. hey. Kenny.

1065
00:51:40.140 --> 00:51:41.552
Kenny. I'm gonna need your medical kit.

1066
00:51:41.576 --> 00:51:42.751
Kenny: On it. Doc.

1067
00:51:42.925 --> 00:51:44.485
Kenny. we're gonna need some more ammo.

1068
00:51:44.623 --> 00:51:46.079
Kenny: Help yourself. You know where to find it.

1069
00:51:46.103 --> 00:51:48.279
Dr. Velie: Ice for this severed ear. Kenny!

1070
00:51:48.453 --> 00:51:50.716
So. what's with all this nighttime commotion?

1071
00:51:50.890 --> 00:51:52.892
Uh. you know. a pair of bank robbers.

1072
00:51:53.066 --> 00:51:54.894
they decided to team up with the sheriff

1073
00:51:55.068 --> 00:51:57.375
after they discovered the Yakuza gold in our vault.

1074
00:51:58.289 --> 00:51:59.986
And they blew up the mayor. Kenny.

1075
00:52:00.595 --> 00:52:03.207
He's on my face. It was really gross.

1076
00:52:03.381 --> 00:52:04.425
Kenny: Oh. shit.

1077
00:52:04.599 --> 00:52:07.080
Oyabun is coming to kill us all.

1078
00:52:08.342 --> 00:52:11.824
You have your devil. We have our Akuma.

1079
00:52:12.390 --> 00:52:14.087
Both fear Oyabun.

1080
00:52:14.609 --> 00:52:18.526
Look. the way I figure it. with the power down.

1081
00:52:18.918 --> 00:52:20.267
they can't get the word out.

1082
00:52:20.441 --> 00:52:22.269
And with the storm being what it is.

1083
00:52:23.009 --> 00:52:25.272
they're stuck here with us.

1084
00:52:26.317 --> 00:52:28.754
And you know. better to be the hunter...

1085
00:52:29.972 --> 00:52:30.973
than the hunted.

1086
00:52:32.061 --> 00:52:32.888
Right?

1087
00:52:33.062 --> 00:52:34.629
- Yeah.
- Yes.

1088
00:52:34.803 --> 00:52:36.196
So. who's up for an affogato?

1089
00:52:37.241 --> 00:52:38.067
On the house.

1090
00:52:38.242 --> 00:52:39.939
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1091
00:52:40.461 --> 00:52:41.767
- [music concludes]
- Open that.

1092
00:52:41.941 --> 00:52:44.944
Oh. damn. Oh. God. Gimme some tape.

1093
00:52:45.118 --> 00:52:46.293
Where's Olive?

1094
00:52:46.467 --> 00:52:47.792
Lori: She's in the car. sweetheart.

1095
00:52:47.816 --> 00:52:49.166
We left the heater on. remember?

1096
00:52:50.123 --> 00:52:53.474
So. it's just us three versus this entire whack-ass town?

1097
00:52:53.648 --> 00:52:55.389
Well. usually. when you rob a bank.

1098
00:52:55.563 --> 00:52:57.130
there are consequences.

1099
00:52:57.304 --> 00:52:59.176
Although this. this is a new one.

1100
00:53:00.742 --> 00:53:02.179
We just wanted something.

1101
00:53:02.657 --> 00:53:04.616
If we get through whatever the fuck this is.

1102
00:53:04.790 --> 00:53:06.313
that'll be something.

1103
00:53:07.009 --> 00:53:09.490
[grunting] Okay. What's the plan?

1104
00:53:09.969 --> 00:53:12.319
We're gonna go to the police station.

1105
00:53:12.493 --> 00:53:15.627
They got a snowplow there. We'll get the fuck out of Dodge.

1106
00:53:15.801 --> 00:53:18.586
Okay. I can drive a snowplow.

1107
00:53:18.760 --> 00:53:20.371
Ulysses: Then you're the man.

1108
00:53:20.545 --> 00:53:21.981
- Let's go. Let's go.
- Lori: Okay.

1109
00:53:22.808 --> 00:53:24.505
[wind gusting]

1110
00:53:24.679 --> 00:53:26.203
Ulysses: Come on. Mr. Plow.

1111
00:53:30.076 --> 00:53:31.208
[automatic gunfire]

1112
00:53:33.514 --> 00:53:35.124
[alarm blaring]

1113
00:53:37.649 --> 00:53:40.042
- [alarm blaring]
- Go! Go!

1114
00:53:40.869 --> 00:53:43.916
Ulysses: I'm okay. He hit the vest! Get out of here!

1115
00:53:44.090 --> 00:53:45.657
We'll meet at the police station!

1116
00:53:46.701 --> 00:53:47.701
Stop!

1117
00:53:49.313 --> 00:53:51.184
Maynard: Iookie what I hooked.

1118
00:53:55.014 --> 00:53:56.668
- [grunts]
- [gun firing]

1119
00:53:57.669 --> 00:53:59.932
[grunts. pants]

1120
00:54:03.152 --> 00:54:05.633
Hello. Sheriff. Eat bar!

1121
00:54:05.807 --> 00:54:07.679
[both grunt]

1122
00:54:28.352 --> 00:54:31.050
[grunting continues]

1123
00:54:32.399 --> 00:54:34.706
You're a slippery little fishy. ain't ya?

1124
00:54:36.751 --> 00:54:39.014
[both grunt]

1125
00:54:40.712 --> 00:54:42.366
God damn it! Stay down!

1126
00:54:46.718 --> 00:54:49.851
- What the hell. man?
- What is wrong with you people?

1127
00:54:50.025 --> 00:54:51.549
We looked you up and we chose you

1128
00:54:51.723 --> 00:54:54.203
because of your reputation for not giving a shit.

1129
00:54:54.378 --> 00:54:56.293
Why'd you decide to start now?

1130
00:54:57.206 --> 00:54:58.556
I'm not myself lately.

1131
00:55:00.775 --> 00:55:01.994
[groans]

1132
00:55:04.910 --> 00:55:07.434
- [screams]
- [Ulysses grunts]

1133
00:55:08.740 --> 00:55:11.917
[yelps. screams]

1134
00:55:13.788 --> 00:55:15.573
God damn.

1135
00:55:16.617 --> 00:55:18.097
- God...
- [grunts]

1136
00:55:18.271 --> 00:55:21.013
[alarm continues blaring]

1137
00:55:30.457 --> 00:55:31.545
[tense music playing]

1138
00:55:31.719 --> 00:55:33.895
[gun firing in distance]

1139
00:55:34.069 --> 00:55:37.246
Ulysses: Heh. Old-fashioned stump removers.

1140
00:55:37.943 --> 00:55:39.901
[gun firing in distance]

1141
00:55:40.075 --> 00:55:42.295
[guns firing]

1142
00:55:45.254 --> 00:55:46.255
I'm out.

1143
00:55:46.430 --> 00:55:47.590
- Huh?
- I don't have anymore.

1144
00:55:48.475 --> 00:55:49.955
[guns clicking empty]

1145
00:55:50.129 --> 00:55:52.392
[pants. grunts]

1146
00:55:57.092 --> 00:55:59.399
Was that a mailman? What?

1147
00:56:01.967 --> 00:56:03.577
You stole a gold brick?

1148
00:56:05.013 --> 00:56:06.101
Of course I did.

1149
00:56:08.756 --> 00:56:10.367
- [grunts]
- [groans]

1150
00:56:11.933 --> 00:56:13.370
[both grunt]

1151
00:56:17.635 --> 00:56:18.766
[groans]

1152
00:56:20.986 --> 00:56:22.074
[groans]

1153
00:56:29.168 --> 00:56:31.083
[metal creaking]

1154
00:56:40.005 --> 00:56:41.005
[gun clicking]

1155
00:56:41.093 --> 00:56:45.358
[trigger continues clicking]

1156
00:56:45.532 --> 00:56:48.187
- [metal creaking]
- [music concludes]

1157
00:56:51.277 --> 00:56:54.323
[sighs] Physics. bitch.

1158
00:56:58.545 --> 00:56:59.807
Is he okay?

1159
00:56:59.981 --> 00:57:02.027
Um. no.

1160
00:57:02.506 --> 00:57:05.247
- [guns firing]
- Go! Go!

1161
00:57:06.161 --> 00:57:07.162
Keith: Go!

1162
00:57:09.513 --> 00:57:11.253
Hold your fire! Hold your fire!

1163
00:57:18.565 --> 00:57:19.871
They murdered James.

1164
00:57:21.525 --> 00:57:23.004
They murdered our mailman.

1165
00:57:24.745 --> 00:57:26.225
Oh. what fresh hell is this?

1166
00:57:26.399 --> 00:57:28.096
Mike: Whoa. be careful with that. Father.

1167
00:57:28.270 --> 00:57:30.664
[chuckling] It's only a flare.

1168
00:57:32.623 --> 00:57:34.973
Hey. there's another one. It's okay.

1169
00:57:35.147 --> 00:57:36.235
[screams]

1170
00:57:37.454 --> 00:57:39.281
[all scream]

1171
00:57:40.761 --> 00:57:41.806
Clayton!

1172
00:57:43.068 --> 00:57:44.548
Go. go. go. go. go. go. go. go!

1173
00:57:44.722 --> 00:57:46.002
- Mike!
- Mike: I got it. Blaine!

1174
00:57:46.071 --> 00:57:47.289
- I got it! I got it.
- Mike...

1175
00:57:47.464 --> 00:57:48.824
Officer: What are you doing. Mike?

1176
00:57:48.900 --> 00:57:50.510
- God's sakes.
- [pants]

1177
00:57:54.035 --> 00:57:57.256
See that. Blaine? I'm a hero.

1178
00:57:59.040 --> 00:58:00.302
[all yelp]

1179
00:58:01.042 --> 00:58:02.174
Mike!

1180
00:58:03.044 --> 00:58:04.219
Oh. he's gone.

1181
00:58:05.917 --> 00:58:07.614
- [groans]
- [ground rumbles]

1182
00:58:09.398 --> 00:58:10.574
Yeah. no thank you.

1183
00:58:11.270 --> 00:58:13.838
[men shouting. screaming]

1184
00:58:19.931 --> 00:58:22.629
[groaning]

1185
00:58:22.803 --> 00:58:26.938
[hip-hop music playing]

1186
00:58:27.112 --> 00:58:32.030
[man rapping in Japanese]

1187
00:58:35.294 --> 00:58:36.338
[speaking in Japanese]

1188
00:58:41.169 --> 00:58:43.215
[in Japanese] Ten fucking hours...

1189
00:58:45.434 --> 00:58:46.566
My ass aches.

1190
00:58:47.785 --> 00:58:48.829
[music concludes]

1191
00:58:49.003 --> 00:58:50.483
[engine sputtering]

1192
00:58:51.440 --> 00:58:53.051
[ominous music playing]

1193
00:58:59.840 --> 00:59:01.363
[engine continues sputtering]

1194
00:59:11.199 --> 00:59:12.960
[in English] I thought you knew how to drive one of these.

1195
00:59:12.984 --> 00:59:16.683
Yeah. I do. But. you know. I do.

1196
00:59:17.510 --> 00:59:18.946
- I... I did.
- [clicking buttons]

1197
00:59:19.120 --> 00:59:20.818
It's just... it's just...

1198
00:59:20.992 --> 00:59:23.603
[engine continues sputtering]

1199
00:59:24.386 --> 00:59:26.321
Lori: Remember when you said you could drive a train?

1200
00:59:26.345 --> 00:59:27.781
And that was bullshit. too.

1201
00:59:29.304 --> 00:59:31.045
- [engine revving]
- Yeah. [Chuckles]

1202
00:59:31.219 --> 00:59:32.219
- See?
- Yeah.

1203
00:59:32.351 --> 00:59:33.657
- Yeah.
- [exhales]

1204
00:59:35.223 --> 00:59:37.965
Keith: It's the matter of going forwards. right?

1205
00:59:38.662 --> 00:59:40.185
- [gun firing]
- Give me that.

1206
00:59:40.359 --> 00:59:41.534
[tense music playing]

1207
00:59:41.708 --> 00:59:44.145
You're spoiling everything.

1208
00:59:44.319 --> 00:59:45.973
[air hissing]

1209
00:59:46.626 --> 00:59:48.367
- Oh no.
- [metal groaning]

1210
00:59:48.541 --> 00:59:50.021
Help! Sheriff. help!

1211
00:59:51.326 --> 00:59:52.501
[both yelp]

1212
00:59:52.676 --> 00:59:54.416
- [pants]
- [music concludes]

1213
01:00:00.422 --> 01:00:01.206
Hey.

1214
01:00:01.380 --> 01:00:02.380
[both yelp]

1215
01:00:02.511 --> 01:00:03.861
Ulysses: Oh. my bad.

1216
01:00:04.165 --> 01:00:07.212
I should have knocked. Can you drive this thing?

1217
01:00:07.386 --> 01:00:09.431
[sighs] Yeah. I think so.

1218
01:00:09.606 --> 01:00:11.303
Okay. well. get to a hospital.

1219
01:00:11.477 --> 01:00:14.175
- You're not coming with us?
- No. I'm sticking around.

1220
01:00:15.089 --> 01:00:18.223
I'm tired of running away from every goddamn thing.

1221
01:00:18.658 --> 01:00:21.008
And you consider this your second chance.

1222
01:00:21.182 --> 01:00:23.315
You take that gold brick. eh?

1223
01:00:24.490 --> 01:00:26.492
And go build something good out of it.

1224
01:00:27.101 --> 01:00:28.537
Take care of yourselves.

1225
01:00:30.888 --> 01:00:32.237
[door whirring]

1226
01:00:33.281 --> 01:00:34.631
[epic music playing]

1227
01:00:42.203 --> 01:00:43.335
Go.

1228
01:00:47.295 --> 01:00:49.341
Lori: How do we even sell a gold brick?

1229
01:00:49.907 --> 01:00:51.256
Break it in half?

1230
01:00:51.430 --> 01:00:53.780
Keith: Well. haven't thought that far ahead.

1231
01:01:01.614 --> 01:01:03.268
Damn it. Where could they have gone?

1232
01:01:03.442 --> 01:01:04.791
It's a small town.

1233
01:01:04.965 --> 01:01:06.445
- [engine rumbling]
- Hey.

1234
01:01:07.751 --> 01:01:09.274
That's our plow.

1235
01:01:09.622 --> 01:01:11.687
Dr. Velie: That ain't Ulysses. He ain't the running type.

1236
01:01:11.711 --> 01:01:13.713
Woman: Well. where's he gonna hide?

1237
01:01:13.887 --> 01:01:16.455
- Police station.
- Let's get him.

1238
01:01:30.077 --> 01:01:31.644
- Whoa! Jeez!
- Lori: Stop! Stop!

1239
01:01:31.818 --> 01:01:32.906
There's Olive.

1240
01:01:38.042 --> 01:01:40.087
- [Olive barking]
- Hey. sweet girl.

1241
01:01:40.261 --> 01:01:42.786
- Good girl. Come on.
- [Olive barks]

1242
01:01:42.960 --> 01:01:44.483
[whimpering]

1243
01:01:45.702 --> 01:01:46.790
Let's go.

1244
01:01:57.017 --> 01:01:58.932
- Let's go home.
- [Olive barking]

1245
01:01:59.106 --> 01:02:02.066
Keith: Yeah. Olive. Fuck this place.

1246
01:02:15.644 --> 01:02:16.820
[racks gun]

1247
01:02:18.517 --> 01:02:19.692
[music concludes]

1248
01:02:21.433 --> 01:02:22.695
[pants]

1249
01:02:23.696 --> 01:02:24.741
[groans]

1250
01:02:26.655 --> 01:02:27.744
[coughs]

1251
01:02:29.049 --> 01:02:30.703
[wheezes] Moira.

1252
01:02:33.532 --> 01:02:34.533
Hey. lawman.

1253
01:02:36.665 --> 01:02:38.015
[wheezing] You don't...

1254
01:02:38.406 --> 01:02:40.757
you don't happen to have a drink on you. do you?

1255
01:02:41.583 --> 01:02:45.022
Now. what kind of bartender would I be... if I didn't?

1256
01:02:47.024 --> 01:02:49.200
- Let's trade.
- [groans]

1257
01:02:53.378 --> 01:02:55.162
Uh-uh. fucking slowly.

1258
01:02:56.076 --> 01:02:57.208
[sighs]

1259
01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:03.997
[groans]

1260
01:03:14.051 --> 01:03:16.227
Well. drink up...

1261
01:03:18.533 --> 01:03:20.753
so. we can all clean up this mess you made

1262
01:03:20.927 --> 01:03:24.235
before the Yakuza turn up and kill every single one of us.

1263
01:03:24.409 --> 01:03:25.627
You. too. huh?

1264
01:03:26.367 --> 01:03:28.805
Just doing what I need to to survive.

1265
01:03:28.979 --> 01:03:30.328
Ulysses: At what cost?

1266
01:03:31.590 --> 01:03:33.244
[chuckles mirthlessly] My soul.

1267
01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:36.377
Although. they're cheap nowadays.

1268
01:03:36.551 --> 01:03:38.510
Hell. you sold yours. didn't you?

1269
01:03:39.380 --> 01:03:40.904
I didn't sell mine.

1270
01:03:42.906 --> 01:03:44.037
I lost it.

1271
01:03:46.431 --> 01:03:47.562
How did you know?

1272
01:03:47.736 --> 01:03:49.608
Bartenders hear a lot of bullshit.

1273
01:03:51.784 --> 01:03:54.221
You get really good at sniffing out the lies.

1274
01:03:55.875 --> 01:04:00.053
Your story was true right until the end. am I right?

1275
01:04:04.275 --> 01:04:06.190
The girl didn't kill her dad.

1276
01:04:07.844 --> 01:04:08.888
You did.

1277
01:04:14.676 --> 01:04:15.852
I shot him...

1278
01:04:18.028 --> 01:04:20.682
right between the eyes for what he'd done.

1279
01:04:24.991 --> 01:04:26.471
I figured it was justice.

1280
01:04:28.777 --> 01:04:30.301
Now. I don't know.

1281
01:04:31.302 --> 01:04:34.000
I've been avoiding making any choices since then.

1282
01:04:35.001 --> 01:04:38.135
just watching life from the sidelines.

1283
01:04:38.831 --> 01:04:40.398
That's my truth.

1284
01:04:41.442 --> 01:04:44.532
Now. you go. What happened to Gunderson?

1285
01:04:44.706 --> 01:04:46.099
I already told mine.

1286
01:04:46.273 --> 01:04:47.666
Me. fish? Fuck no.

1287
01:04:48.623 --> 01:04:50.234
Probably the only one in town who don't.

1288
01:04:51.844 --> 01:04:54.325
Gunderson. he had a fishing pole in one hand.

1289
01:04:54.499 --> 01:04:57.284
like this one. and an auger in the other.

1290
01:04:57.937 --> 01:05:00.244
So. my guess is he thought he was going ice fishing.

1291
01:05:01.201 --> 01:05:03.464
Who the fuck goes ice fishing with a fly rod?

1292
01:05:03.638 --> 01:05:05.118
[sighs] No one.

1293
01:05:06.815 --> 01:05:09.079
I lied. I killed him.

1294
01:05:09.688 --> 01:05:11.690
Because he wanted a bigger cut of the deal?

1295
01:05:11.864 --> 01:05:15.215
Because he wanted out of the job. of...

1296
01:05:15.389 --> 01:05:18.958
[sighing] ...the town. the arrangement.

1297
01:05:19.306 --> 01:05:20.307
Why?

1298
01:05:22.048 --> 01:05:23.180
Missed his kid.

1299
01:05:24.094 --> 01:05:25.834
This town made him choose.

1300
01:05:26.705 --> 01:05:29.534
It's a small town in every way. you know.

1301
01:05:30.230 --> 01:05:33.016
- small-minded.
- Yeah. I get that.

1302
01:05:34.713 --> 01:05:37.759
- And no one gets out.
- Not even him.

1303
01:05:39.196 --> 01:05:40.980
So. you got him drunk and...

1304
01:05:42.547 --> 01:05:43.809
walked him out and...

1305
01:05:43.983 --> 01:05:45.724
Watched him freeze to death...

1306
01:05:46.943 --> 01:05:50.163
which takes longer than you'd think.

1307
01:05:50.903 --> 01:05:54.733
Unless you're wet. which he was.
because I poured water on him.

1308
01:05:55.995 --> 01:05:58.084
But I learned something about myself that night.

1309
01:05:59.346 --> 01:06:01.087
- What's that?
- [sighs]

1310
01:06:01.261 --> 01:06:02.915
That I can do what needs to be done.

1311
01:06:04.177 --> 01:06:07.224
- What happened to you?
- Nothing I didn't choose.

1312
01:06:10.009 --> 01:06:11.968
Like I said. that's a cool belt.

1313
01:06:15.058 --> 01:06:16.407
[groans]

1314
01:06:19.976 --> 01:06:21.586
What the fuck. Sheriff?

1315
01:06:22.804 --> 01:06:23.936
Tell me about it.

1316
01:06:25.851 --> 01:06:27.940
I think he would have wanted you to have this.

1317
01:06:28.114 --> 01:06:30.073
especially in light of current events.

1318
01:06:31.770 --> 01:06:32.945
[sighs]

1319
01:06:35.252 --> 01:06:36.993
Let's go. Deputy.

1320
01:06:37.950 --> 01:06:40.257
This shit storm is only gonna get worse.

1321
01:06:53.183 --> 01:06:54.183
Whoa!

1322
01:06:56.447 --> 01:07:00.277
[engine revving]

1323
01:07:00.451 --> 01:07:01.539
Hey. Blaine.

1324
01:07:02.801 --> 01:07:04.629
- [engine revving]
- Light 'em up!

1325
01:07:08.067 --> 01:07:09.416
Bulletproof. motherfuckers.

1326
01:07:09.590 --> 01:07:11.418
[guns firing. shots ricocheting]

1327
01:07:11.592 --> 01:07:13.464
[engine revving]

1328
01:07:13.638 --> 01:07:15.292
[tires screeching]

1329
01:07:16.641 --> 01:07:17.424
- [screams]
- [squelching]

1330
01:07:17.598 --> 01:07:18.598
Whoa!

1331
01:07:19.035 --> 01:07:20.862
[shots ricocheting]

1332
01:07:21.472 --> 01:07:22.690
[laughs]

1333
01:07:23.822 --> 01:07:25.780
- [groans]
- Hey. Blaine!

1334
01:07:27.652 --> 01:07:29.523
- Yeah. Joe?
- Damn it.

1335
01:07:30.176 --> 01:07:32.265
Did we leave anyone back at the bank?

1336
01:07:33.571 --> 01:07:34.615
No. Joe.

1337
01:07:35.877 --> 01:07:36.965
And the vault?

1338
01:07:37.879 --> 01:07:39.011
Yeah. Joe?

1339
01:07:40.491 --> 01:07:43.668
Is it... still open?

1340
01:07:45.322 --> 01:07:47.846
[tires screeching]

1341
01:07:53.286 --> 01:07:55.419
- [screams]
- [glass shattering]

1342
01:07:58.857 --> 01:08:00.859
[gasps]

1343
01:08:07.213 --> 01:08:08.997
[suspenseful music playing]

1344
01:08:12.088 --> 01:08:13.456
- [radio beeping]
- Ulysses: Yoo-hoo!

1345
01:08:13.480 --> 01:08:14.916
Answer the phone.

1346
01:08:16.918 --> 01:08:21.532
My deputy is currently securing the contents of your vault.

1347
01:08:27.494 --> 01:08:28.539
Securing?

1348
01:08:29.279 --> 01:08:32.282
Ulysses: Bricks of C4 have been planted

1349
01:08:32.586 --> 01:08:37.374
in and amongst the Yakuza's physical deposits. as it were.

1350
01:08:39.419 --> 01:08:44.381
So. to sum up. if I die. it all goes boom.

1351
01:08:44.903 --> 01:08:46.426
And if it goes boom.

1352
01:08:46.600 --> 01:08:49.995
well. them being the Yakuza and all.

1353
01:08:50.735 --> 01:08:52.911
I don't think it ends real well for you.

1354
01:08:54.042 --> 01:08:56.219
If we don't finish this here and now.

1355
01:08:56.393 --> 01:08:57.611
the Yakuza will hunt down

1356
01:08:57.785 --> 01:09:00.353
and kill each and every one of us.

1357
01:09:01.137 --> 01:09:02.486
me included.

1358
01:09:04.575 --> 01:09:06.490
- [music concludes]
- But wait. there's more.

1359
01:09:08.579 --> 01:09:09.928
I've got a proposal.

1360
01:09:13.105 --> 01:09:14.802
We tidy up the bank.

1361
01:09:14.976 --> 01:09:18.415
make it look like an accident. like nothing bad happened.

1362
01:09:19.590 --> 01:09:22.158
Just another Saturday.

1363
01:09:23.246 --> 01:09:24.246
Mm.

1364
01:09:24.943 --> 01:09:28.294
Kenny. you say this is Belgian chocolate?

1365
01:09:28.468 --> 01:09:29.600
Kenny: French.

1366
01:09:29.774 --> 01:09:32.516
Mm. Same difference. you know.

1367
01:09:34.735 --> 01:09:37.129
So. that's your plan?

1368
01:09:38.086 --> 01:09:39.087
That's it.

1369
01:09:41.046 --> 01:09:42.656
Just make it seem like any other day.

1370
01:09:42.830 --> 01:09:44.092
Basically. yeah.

1371
01:09:45.137 --> 01:09:49.185
The Yakuza show up. their treasure is untouched.

1372
01:09:49.707 --> 01:09:52.666
Nothing more than a car accident that set off the alarm.

1373
01:09:52.840 --> 01:09:55.626
Life in Normal is normal. calm.

1374
01:09:57.105 --> 01:10:00.413
Calm... cleans messy.

1375
01:10:01.153 --> 01:10:02.285
That's right.

1376
01:10:03.242 --> 01:10:07.812
Why don't I just kill you right now?

1377
01:10:10.206 --> 01:10:12.295
The only thing your boss is gonna give a shit about

1378
01:10:12.469 --> 01:10:13.774
is that you messed up.

1379
01:10:15.385 --> 01:10:18.214
I say we play the hand that's been dealt to all of us.

1380
01:10:19.693 --> 01:10:23.001
You make us look good. we'll make you look good.

1381
01:10:24.089 --> 01:10:25.482
And maybe you get to keep the rest

1382
01:10:25.656 --> 01:10:27.223
of your goddamn fingers.

1383
01:10:27.397 --> 01:10:29.181
[suspenseful music playing]

1384
01:10:31.531 --> 01:10:35.405
I'm sorry that I. uh... killed your mayor.

1385
01:10:35.883 --> 01:10:37.494
I know you liked him a lot.

1386
01:10:38.799 --> 01:10:41.062
Though. he did seem a bit of an a-hole.

1387
01:10:44.675 --> 01:10:45.675
Okay.

1388
01:10:47.373 --> 01:10:48.809
[clearing throat] What do you say?

1389
01:10:50.246 --> 01:10:54.380
Well. it... isn't much of a plan.

1390
01:10:54.902 --> 01:10:59.255
Well. I'm not much of a sheriff. but I'm all you've got.

1391
01:11:06.131 --> 01:11:08.525
- [radio beeps]
- Hey. Alex.

1392
01:11:09.177 --> 01:11:10.396
Let's a put on a show.

1393
01:11:11.658 --> 01:11:13.530
I'm kind of liking...

1394
01:11:14.966 --> 01:11:15.967
Deputy.

1395
01:11:16.794 --> 01:11:17.838
[radio beeps]

1396
01:11:20.232 --> 01:11:21.233
[slurps]

1397
01:11:22.016 --> 01:11:23.016
Fuck yeah.

1398
01:11:23.148 --> 01:11:24.628
[Japanese pop music playing]

1399
01:11:24.802 --> 01:11:26.762
Ulysses: Come on. people! This is the new Normal!

1400
01:11:26.891 --> 01:11:28.632
It's gotta seem like an accident!

1401
01:11:28.806 --> 01:11:31.199
Like there wasn't a massacre here. you know?

1402
01:11:31.374 --> 01:11:33.245
Bring it in! Bring it in!

1403
01:11:34.072 --> 01:11:35.726
Look for loose limbs!

1404
01:11:36.727 --> 01:11:38.859
Watch for blood splotches.

1405
01:11:39.730 --> 01:11:40.905
Cover 'em up.

1406
01:11:42.036 --> 01:11:45.083
Winter wonderland! Let's go for it. folks.

1407
01:11:45.779 --> 01:11:47.912
Make it nice for our guests.

1408
01:11:48.913 --> 01:11:50.044
Let's bring it around.

1409
01:11:50.654 --> 01:11:54.266
Down there. look for any loose entrails.

1410
01:12:16.419 --> 01:12:18.029
[music concludes]

1411
01:12:18.203 --> 01:12:19.422
Blaine: Swear to God.

1412
01:12:19.596 --> 01:12:22.990
I had no idea about killing Gunderson.

1413
01:12:23.164 --> 01:12:24.564
Ulysses: You believed that bullshit

1414
01:12:24.644 --> 01:12:26.037
about the fishing rod?

1415
01:12:26.211 --> 01:12:27.928
Blaine: Sorry. I'm not much of a fisherman.

1416
01:12:27.952 --> 01:12:29.345
but. yeah. I get your point.

1417
01:12:29.649 --> 01:12:31.912
Ulysses: And you tried to shoot me.

1418
01:12:32.086 --> 01:12:34.611
Blaine: Yeah. I did shoot you. but I didn't kill you.

1419
01:12:34.785 --> 01:12:36.656
That's the important thing.

1420
01:12:37.222 --> 01:12:39.311
We're here together. both of us...

1421
01:12:41.444 --> 01:12:42.445
alive.

1422
01:12:44.751 --> 01:12:45.839
Do you. uh...

1423
01:12:46.362 --> 01:12:48.146
Do you really think this is gonna work?

1424
01:12:50.453 --> 01:12:51.715
You a betting man?

1425
01:12:52.672 --> 01:12:54.457
To my own detriment. to be sure.

1426
01:12:57.111 --> 01:13:00.158
I'd put a Benji on the lay.

1427
01:13:01.681 --> 01:13:04.162
Wait a minute. You're... You're betting against us?

1428
01:13:04.336 --> 01:13:06.991
[Japanese rap music playing in distance]

1429
01:13:08.166 --> 01:13:10.255
Oof. We're fucked. huh?

1430
01:13:10.429 --> 01:13:11.648
[Japanese rap music playing]

1431
01:13:11.822 --> 01:13:14.390
Well. best get into character.

1432
01:13:26.010 --> 01:13:27.664
[music concludes]

1433
01:13:27.838 --> 01:13:30.038
[in Japanese] You got some explaining to do. don't you?

1434
01:13:30.188 --> 01:13:33.191
Yes. I have several explanations.

1435
01:13:33.365 --> 01:13:36.934
[in English] As you can s... Can you... Can you translate?

1436
01:13:38.892 --> 01:13:42.069
As you can see. the storm here was something else.

1437
01:13:42.243 --> 01:13:45.508
It knocked out phones. internet. cell service. hell.

1438
01:13:45.682 --> 01:13:47.379
you name it. it's down.

1439
01:13:47.553 --> 01:13:49.953
- [translator speaking Japanese]
- [in English] Howdy. y'all.

1440
01:13:50.251 --> 01:13:53.124
Oh. he's the interim. like I told you.

1441
01:13:53.298 --> 01:13:56.562
He don't know shit. He's. uh. not too bright.

1442
01:13:56.736 --> 01:13:58.366
Ulysses: Deputy Blaine. you know these folks?

1443
01:13:58.390 --> 01:14:00.063
You want to explain to them they can't come

1444
01:14:00.087 --> 01:14:02.089
tearing through our county in a convoy like this

1445
01:14:02.263 --> 01:14:04.744
without getting a greeting from the law?

1446
01:14:04.918 --> 01:14:07.878
Well. uh. this is actually Pastor Oyabun. Sheriff.

1447
01:14:08.052 --> 01:14:09.662
- Oh. a pastor.
- Mm-hmm.

1448
01:14:09.836 --> 01:14:11.142
He's got a small parish

1449
01:14:11.316 --> 01:14:13.057
just over yonder down near Everton.

1450
01:14:13.231 --> 01:14:15.102
What's his denomination?

1451
01:14:15.842 --> 01:14:18.062
Protestant. Ain't that right?

1452
01:14:18.454 --> 01:14:20.736
[in Japanese] I don't know what
the hell you guys are talking about!

1453
01:14:20.760 --> 01:14:22.160
- [in English] Tell him.
- He's mad.

1454
01:14:22.283 --> 01:14:23.652
Oyabun: [in Japanese] We must get going.

1455
01:14:23.676 --> 01:14:25.199
[in English] What's he upset about?

1456
01:14:25.504 --> 01:14:26.960
- [in Japanese] Bank! Bank!
- Blaine: [in English] I think...

1457
01:14:26.984 --> 01:14:28.899
I think that he wants to go to the bank.

1458
01:14:29.073 --> 01:14:30.727
[in Japanese] Are we going now or what?

1459
01:14:30.901 --> 01:14:32.400
[in English] He can't go to the bank. We've got the...

1460
01:14:32.424 --> 01:14:34.382
- Yeah. yeah. but...
- There's people down.

1461
01:14:34.557 --> 01:14:35.993
- It's true that...
- Hey!

1462
01:14:36.167 --> 01:14:37.690
Hey. hey.

1463
01:14:37.864 --> 01:14:40.171
- We'll make an exception.
- Make an exception.

1464
01:14:40.345 --> 01:14:43.043
- We'll give you an escort.
- Blaine: Follow us. Let's go.

1465
01:14:43.217 --> 01:14:44.741
[in Japanese] Let's go. hurry up.

1466
01:14:44.915 --> 01:14:46.394
You start driving.

1467
01:14:46.569 --> 01:14:48.484
Ulysses: [in English] Okay. Deputy Blaine.

1468
01:14:48.658 --> 01:14:51.269
let's take our guests the long way around.

1469
01:14:52.139 --> 01:14:54.490
Give them a little more time to fix up the bank.

1470
01:14:56.796 --> 01:14:58.581
[in Japanese] How can these assholes

1471
01:14:58.755 --> 01:15:00.713
get lost on a straight road?

1472
01:15:00.887 --> 01:15:02.280
[tense music playing]

1473
01:15:02.454 --> 01:15:03.736
[in English] Those aren't the best shoes.

1474
01:15:03.760 --> 01:15:05.120
Ulysses: Yes. sir. Right this way.

1475
01:15:05.283 --> 01:15:06.565
Blaine: So. just watch your step. Come on.

1476
01:15:06.589 --> 01:15:08.112
Oyabun: [in Japanese] This is it?

1477
01:15:08.286 --> 01:15:08.678
Ulysses: [in English] Well. it doesn't look good.

1478
01:15:08.852 --> 01:15:10.244
I know.

1479
01:15:10.418 --> 01:15:11.961
Oyabun: [in Japanese] My money better be safe.

1480
01:15:11.985 --> 01:15:12.551
Ulysses: [in English] Careful of the snow.

1481
01:15:12.725 --> 01:15:13.725
[device beeps]

1482
01:15:19.602 --> 01:15:21.168
The driver was killed on impact.

1483
01:15:21.342 --> 01:15:23.059
as was the bank manager and security guard.

1484
01:15:23.083 --> 01:15:24.452
- [in Japanese] Where's Haru?
- Killed.

1485
01:15:24.476 --> 01:15:26.043
And the vault?

1486
01:15:26.217 --> 01:15:27.977
[in English] Sheriff. you mind if I show him the vault?

1487
01:15:28.001 --> 01:15:30.395
The church has some papers in their safe deposit box.

1488
01:15:30.569 --> 01:15:33.137
- Yeah. sure. go ahead.
- Blaine: Good. Yeah. this way.

1489
01:15:34.181 --> 01:15:35.966
Ulysses: The building's in fine shape.

1490
01:15:36.140 --> 01:15:38.359
Uh. actually. it wasn't a load-bearing wall.

1491
01:15:38.534 --> 01:15:39.970
Excuse me. Uh...

1492
01:15:40.144 --> 01:15:44.191
As you can see. the vault. it's untouched.

1493
01:15:44.365 --> 01:15:46.672
Excuse me. Pristine.

1494
01:15:46.846 --> 01:15:49.153
Whoa! The church has done well. huh?

1495
01:15:54.158 --> 01:15:55.855
- Pretty color. huh?
- [music concludes]

1496
01:15:56.029 --> 01:15:57.378
[in Japanese] Now. who's hungry?

1497
01:15:57.553 --> 01:15:59.555
["Hot Rod Hop" playing]

1498
01:15:59.729 --> 01:16:01.861
♪ There's a small garage On the edge of town ♪

1499
01:16:02.035 --> 01:16:04.690
♪ Where the hot rods go When the sun goes down ♪

1500
01:16:04.864 --> 01:16:06.736
♪ The place belongs To a Mr. Jones ♪

1501
01:16:06.910 --> 01:16:08.540
- ♪ Who repairs hot rods... ♪
- [song concludes]

1502
01:16:08.564 --> 01:16:10.478
Ulysses: Why did you invite them out for food?

1503
01:16:12.568 --> 01:16:15.309
I only know. like. four phrases in Japanese. and...

1504
01:16:16.441 --> 01:16:17.616
I guess I panicked.

1505
01:16:21.185 --> 01:16:23.143
Is your boss enjoying the meatloaf?

1506
01:16:23.927 --> 01:16:25.276
[speaking Japanese]

1507
01:16:25.842 --> 01:16:28.018
[in English] This is divine.

1508
01:16:30.237 --> 01:16:31.804
Your English is very good. sir.

1509
01:16:32.762 --> 01:16:34.154
I watch a lot of Friends.

1510
01:16:34.546 --> 01:16:36.287
Who's in for mimosas?

1511
01:16:36.461 --> 01:16:39.377
- [men shouting affirmation]
- Blaine: Should I make a toast?

1512
01:16:40.813 --> 01:16:43.642
- Don't.
- Blaine: Uh. excuse me. Um...

1513
01:16:45.905 --> 01:16:49.343
[chuckling nervously] I. uh... I'd like to propose a toast.

1514
01:16:49.517 --> 01:16:51.607
Um... You know. I'm. uh.

1515
01:16:51.781 --> 01:16:54.610
what you might call a "people person."

1516
01:16:54.784 --> 01:16:57.874
So. this toast is to friendship. I think it's important

1517
01:16:58.048 --> 01:16:59.745
that I take credit for this event.

1518
01:16:59.919 --> 01:17:02.182
When I become the next sheriff of Normal.

1519
01:17:02.356 --> 01:17:06.056
there will be many more opportunities to come together

1520
01:17:06.230 --> 01:17:09.625
and break bread. strengthening our link.

1521
01:17:09.799 --> 01:17:14.630
And with Pastor Oyabun and his friendly. friendly.

1522
01:17:14.804 --> 01:17:19.417
um. congregation. I think this is a new chapter

1523
01:17:19.591 --> 01:17:22.812
for our town and our happy arrangement.

1524
01:17:22.986 --> 01:17:26.903
So. I'd like to say thank you for all your help

1525
01:17:27.077 --> 01:17:31.298
and to many. many more years

1526
01:17:31.472 --> 01:17:38.088
of friendly people helping other friendly people.

1527
01:17:48.794 --> 01:17:50.361
[all gasping]

1528
01:17:51.667 --> 01:17:52.755
[gasps]

1529
01:17:53.930 --> 01:17:54.930
Arata: Please!

1530
01:17:55.671 --> 01:17:58.064
[sobs hysterically]

1531
01:17:58.804 --> 01:17:59.892
Oh. shit.

1532
01:18:00.066 --> 01:18:01.546
[song continues]

1533
01:18:01.720 --> 01:18:04.462
♪ Pop. pop. peep-peep-peep ♪

1534
01:18:04.636 --> 01:18:08.509
♪ Pop. pop Peep. pop. pop. oh pop ♪

1535
01:18:08.684 --> 01:18:10.816
- ♪ Pop. pop ♪
- [song concludes]

1536
01:18:17.344 --> 01:18:21.958
["When You're in Love With a Beautiful Woman" playing]

1537
01:18:27.790 --> 01:18:29.269
[roars]

1538
01:18:29.443 --> 01:18:32.664
[crashing. shouting]

1539
01:18:32.838 --> 01:18:34.318
[shots firing]

1540
01:18:38.148 --> 01:18:39.149
[groans]

1541
01:18:44.458 --> 01:18:45.503
[groans] Asshole!

1542
01:18:45.677 --> 01:18:48.724
- [guns firing]
- [men shouting]

1543
01:18:48.898 --> 01:18:50.290
